title: no icing apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and apples.
Mix together with spoon.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top of cake will have a crunchy top.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: sugar free rhubarb dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pie plate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with vegetable spray. Combine chicken, cream of chicken soup and sour cream and put in casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers over chicken mixture. Drizzle margarine over cracker crumbs. Sprinkle poppy seeds over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Serve with golden and red apple slices.

title: steve's grilled potatoes
directions: Wrap potatoes, onion, peppers and spices in aluminum foil twice.
Place on grill on low heat.
Turn every 15 minutes for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: main dish cheese pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat well.
Stir in cheese.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix Jello and Knox packages together.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add Cool Whip and stir again until dissolved.
Pour mixture into a 9x12-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator until thick.
Cut into 1 or 2 inch squares.
The Cool Whip will seperate and rise to the top and give the Jello a nice layered look.

title: lovers delight
directions: Mix together shortening, salt and vanilla; add remaining ingredients. After mixing all these ingredients together, spread real thin on cookie sheet. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top. Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup brown sugar and spread on top. Bake for 20 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo and crackers together.
In greased casserole, layer crackers on bottom, then broccoli, cheese and crackers; repeat. Have crumbs on top.
Pour soup, thinned with a little milk, over all.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 360°.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Raise frozen bread according to package directions.

Roll bread dough out lengthwise; spread cooked sausage down the middle. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; then spread beaten egg on top. Pinch dough sides together; bake at 350° with bread seam down, for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is good served with salsa sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Drain fat.
Add Ragu and all ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil. Simmer on low 15 minutes.
In greased casserole, alternate layers of sauce and potatoes, beginning and ending with sauce.
Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: donna's "monster" cookies
directions: Mix together in extra large bowl.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 11 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: ornament fun
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll out with rolling pin.
Use different shaped cookie cutters and cut shapes out of dough.
Put small hole in top of shape.
Grease pan and bake 1 hour at 300°. Let set several hours and let children paint ornaments with magic markers or paint and hang on tree.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with next 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine next 8 ingredients; mix lightly.
Spread mixture evenly over potatoes.
Spoon 1/4 cup catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except spaghetti together and pour over spaghetti.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces and steam 5 minutes. Heat oil in wok. Beat the eggs and set aside. Cook onions in wok first. Add eggs and cook until firm. Add rice. Keep stirring until eggs and rice are well mixed. Add soy sauce, pepper and vegetables. Stir until rice is light brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Combine beef, garlic, onion and rosemary.
Chop until fine in a food processor (or by hand).
Melt the butter in a skillet and stir in the flour.
Cook for a few minutes until smooth and blended.
Slowly add the beef broth. Stir and cook until gravy is thickened, cooking at least 5 minutes to get rid of the raw flour taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil yams for 25 minutes; cool, then peel.
Place yams, butter, vanilla, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in mixing bowl.
Add can of Carnation milk.
Whip at medium speed until all lumps are gone.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: julia's frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream sour cream, sugar, salt and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and pour into muffin cups lined with paper liners. Freeze.
Take out a few minutes before serving.

title: mama's banana cake
directions: Beat eggs, margarine and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add, alternating with soda and milk mixture.
Mix. Last, stir in 1 cup mashed very ripe bananas.
Makes a small cake.
It's a good way to use overripe bananas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Cook and drain egg noodles.
Layer in large, oblong casserole dish.
Then layer cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Mix well.
Layer 3 is hamburger, seasonings, tomatoes and tomato sauce simmered for 10 minutes.
Layer cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or microwave for 20 minutes.

title: sandy's cake
directions: Put ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan as listed; do not stir. Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, vinegar, oil, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Pour over drained carrots, onion and peppers.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 1 month.

title: chicken gumbo sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Also good served over cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; add sauce and water.
Simmer.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 1/2 cups of meat mixture in bottom.
One layer of noodles, then 1/2 Ricotta cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Top with one more layer of noodles, then 1/2 Ricotta cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Pour rest of meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let sit overnight.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients saving 1/4 cup grated cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour combined ingredients into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese, cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chipper cookies
directions: Measure dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in oil, egg and vanilla.
Mixture may seem almost dry.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Boil white sugar and evaporated milk for 4 minutes to soft ball stage.
Cook in heavy pan and stir constantly because it will stick and burn.
Do not scrape crystals off side of pan.
In a large mixing bowl at room temperature, mix milk chocolate, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Fluff, margarine or butter and walnuts.
Pour syrup over ingredients while very hot.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
You need 2 buttered utility dishes or comparable dishes.

title: deer stew
directions: Cook vegetables first to a good boiling roll for about 15 minutes.
Slice deer meat in and cook for about 3 hours on low heat.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter. Add the flour, stirring until blended. Stir in the cream and cooking sherry or water; cook until thickened, stirring constantly. When bubbly, cook and stir 2 more minutes. Blend in soup until smooth; remove from heat and set aside. Place broccoli in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with rice and half the sauce. Top with chicken. Stir shredded cheese into the remaining sauce; pour over chicken. Melt remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: copper pennies
directions: May use fresh carrots.
(Peel and cook until tender.)
Let cool.
Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Stir to mix. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Crumble corned beef into greased 12 x 8-inch glass pan. Spread with dressing and sauerkraut.
Cover with cheese.
Toss crumbled bread with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Add taco mix, enchilada sauce, cheese and sour cream or dip to hamburger. Grease pan, 9 x 13. Layer this way:
1. Sauce, 2. Tortillas, 3. Sour cream or dip, 4. Cheese, 5. Hamburger. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes uncovered and 45 minutes covered.

title: shake-it-up chex party mix
directions: In small microwave bowl, melt butter.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into large Ziploc bag.
Pour butter over cereals in bag.
Seal tightly. Shake bag until pieces are evenly coated.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat liquid ingredients together, then add dry ones, adding bran flakes last.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.)
Use large mixing bowl.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soups and broth and mix.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; add onion, mushrooms and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Spoon 1/2 the spaghetti into a buttered casserole; add 1/2 the chicken.
Top with 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat with remaining spaghetti, chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle pimientos over top or stir in sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix the first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into an oblong dish coated with vegetable spray.
Pour margarine over top of the mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown. Yields 12 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix together rice, soup, broccoli and 1/2 jar Cheez Whiz.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add 1 1/4 jars of Ragu with meat and heat until warm.
In an oblong pan, cover bottom with sauce. Add noodles, then cheese, ending with sauce.
Pour reserved Ragu over top.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Take out and cover with foil for 30 minutes before serving.

title: beef and tomato pie
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Remove from the heat. Stir in ketchup and salt; set aside. Spoon meat mixture into precooked pie shell. Sprinkle with tomatoes. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; bake 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: cajun pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops as needed.
Pat dry.
Combine seasonings, then coat chops with seasonings with mixture on both sides.
Heat butter over high heat until it starts to brown; put chops in pan and reduce heat to medium.
Fry chops on both sides until dark brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bacon and buttermilk mashed potatoes
directions: Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook, peel and mash potatoes. Add buttermilk and butter; mash again.
Add chives.
Top with bacon.

title: mattie boykin's chicken casserole
directions: Cut up fryer and boil until tender. Take chicken off bones and cut into bite size pieces. Stir together with next 3 ingredients. Add crumbled crackers, reserving a few to put on top.
Add enough chicken broth to make juicy.
Put remaining crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: orange nut balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into very fine crumbs; put into bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls (approximately 1 inch).
Let stand for 1 hour on waxed paper. Place in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: In saucepan, melt half of butter.
Add sugar, flour and juice from pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Pour in casserole dish over pineapple.
Melt rest of butter in same pan.
Crumble crackers in butter.
Top pineapple with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange cranberry relish
directions: Peel and section oranges.
In food processor, process orange sections and cranberries.
Stir in sugar, nuts and peels.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
May be frozen up to 6 months.

title: daffodillies
directions: Separate dough into 12 pieces.
Using kitchen scissors, cut rolls from outside, almost to center, to form 8 petals.
Place on cookie sheet.
Make deep indentation in center of each roll.
In small bowl combine cream cheese, butter, mustard and dill weed until smooth.
Fill center of rolls with heaping teaspoonfuls. Bake in a 375° oven on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 13 minutes. Serve warm.

title: crawfish spaghetti
directions: In a small amount of oil, saute the onion and bell pepper. When the onion is clear, add the roux and stir well.
Add enough water to make a semi-thick gravy.
Cook until the roux is well dissolved.
Add the mushroom soup and seasonings and continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Add the crawfish tails and cook another 7 minutes.
Pour this mixture over the cooked and drained spaghetti and stir well.
Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Pour the spaghetti into the casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° just long enough for the cheese to melt.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onion and salt in a large bowl of water; place a plate on top of this and let stand for 2 hours.
Boil sugar, vinegar, water and pickling spices together until it comes to a full boil.
Drain the cukes and onions and pack in plastic containers...you can use any empty plastic containers you might have around, i.e., butter containers and the like.
Pour the hot mixture over these.
Seal with plastic lids and store in freezer. Keeps for months in the freezer.
Voila!
Just thaw out when ready to use!

title: iced almonds
directions: Heat almonds, sugar and butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, until almonds are toasted and sugar is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread nuts on a sheet of foil; sprinkle with salt.
Break into 2 or 3 nut clusters.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Combine milk and eggs; add to cake mix and dry pudding mix with wooden spoon (not mixer).
Add chips and nuts.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake bounces back at touch.
May pour a glaze on top, if desired.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers, slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.

title: chuck's hawaiian chicken
directions: Note:
Use skinless chicken breasts and marinate in teriyaki sauce for 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, undrained pineapple and mashed bananas.
Pour half the mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour until firm.
Beat cream cheese with sour cream and sugar.
Spread over chilled layer.
Gently spoon remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Top with one-half roll of Ritz crackers and 1 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time, beating for 5 minutes after each addition. Blend in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Pour into prebaked pie shell. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.

title: hard tack candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water in large, heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Boil, while stirring, until 310° or until beads form in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto cold, buttered marble.
Cut into pieces and drop into powdered sugar.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak bran in milk.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in milk and bran.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Stir until just moistened.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: texas style beans
directions: Brown ground beef with dry onion soup mix.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: best refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour.
Beat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Put in large bowl as it rises slightly in the fridge.
This will keep for a week to 10 days.
About 3 hours before using rolls, form into desired shape using only enough flour to handle.
Place in greased pan and let rise at room temperature for remaining time.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts and save broth.
Roll out dumplings according to recipe on box (2 cups Bisquick and 2/3 cup milk).
(I make up about 3 to 4 times, depending on how many people.)
This recipe will feed about 8 people.

title: cashew blondies (brownies)
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; add to oil mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in cashews.
Spread in a well-greased 8-inch square pan and bake in 350° oven until done, about 20 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: strawberry cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Use directions on cake box to make cake.
In a mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Frost cooled cake.
Spiral fresh strawberries on top until completely covered.
Slice and serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up washed and drained lettuce in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Cover lettuce with sliced cauliflower.
Add peas (do not allow them to thaw first).	Cover these layers with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with Italian dressing mix and then cheese.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with plastic wrap.

title: party chicken
directions: Cover the bottom of a flat, greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with dried beef. Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon. Arrange chicken on dried beef. Mix undiluted soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours or until done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Get flour ready, sift first:
flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening.
Add white sugar first, then brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Add flour all at one time to oatmeal, chocolate tidbits, raisins or coconut.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix all ingredients for first layer and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little boiling water until tender, 5 minutes.
Drain.
In a saucepan, saute carrots and onions in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix, the soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter and remaining 3/4 cup dressing mix.
Toss gently and spread in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer; blend with enough milk to make a creamy consistency.
Blend well, until no large pieces in dip. Chill and serve.

title: grammie sissie's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in a saucepan and heat until the butter melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature and mix together (I use my hands) adding Rice Krispies last.
Roll into small balls and flatten each one slightly with a fork.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove when slightly cooled from cookie sheet.

title: emma cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: banner chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients (sugar and flour). In saucepan, bring butter, Crisco, cocoa and water to boil and pour over flour/sugar mixture. Stir well and add remaining ingredients. Mix well; pour in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: In a large pot, steam chicken pieces, smoked sausage, hot sausage, stew meat, chopped ham and/or pickled meat and crab (if any).
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Toss with an assortment of chopped vegetables.
Serve cold.

title: occident(100% whole wheat bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk, salt, brown sugar and shortening to milk; cool to lukewarm. Add dissolved yeast; mix well.
Add half of the flour; mix well. Work in remainder of flour.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; shape into several balls.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Knead for 10 minutes; place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Punch down; cover and let rise another hour.
Divide in half; cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in greased bread pans. Cover and let rise in warm place, about an hour.
Bake.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Start by cutting corn tortillas in 1 1/2-inch squares. Put aside.
Melt Crisco in fry-pan and add flour and red chili until all mixed together. Slowly add hot water.
This will start to thicken.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well, adding raisins and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat in jam and nutmeg.
Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon water and add to sour cream, then add this to eggs which have been beaten.
Add to butter-sugar mixture, then mix with flour.
Sprinkle small amount of flour over raisins and stir in.
Bake in 350° oven in small loaf pan until done, about 30 minutes.
May be frosted or left plain.

title: new orleans gumbo
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; stir and cover.
Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: spinach mandarin salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Add oranges and almonds and toss with dressing.

title: vegetable and chicken pot pie
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter, add celery and stir over a medium high heat until crisp but tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper and mix well.
Stir in thawed veggies and chicken; heat through.
Spoon into 12 x 8 baking dish.
Heat oven to 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5. Separate dough into 10 biscuits, cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Arrange the biscuits over the hot filling.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chili burgers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form 6 patties.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.
Top with cheese; broil until melted.
Top with salsa on buns.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add last three ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes or until toothpick test comes up clean.

title: hello dollies
directions: In 9x9 pan melt 1 stick oleo. Add in layers: graham cracker crumbs, chocolate tidbits, coconut and nuts. Pour milk over the top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown. Cut while warm and remove from pan after cool. Makes about 30 squares.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Microwave rice and
water
on
High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after
minutes.
Cover	with
plastic wrap and let cool.
Add 1/2
cup
water to raisins and microwave just until softened.
Cover
and
cool.
Then add pudding mixed with milk and nutmeg.
Refrigerate and serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: swedish mocha cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Combine coffee, 1 cup sugar and raisins in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes and cool.
Cream butter, add 1 cup sugar, vanilla and one egg at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and cooked mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a moist cake and stores well.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with hard sauce.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in long pan in the listed order.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Gently remove yolks; place in small bowl.
With fork, finely mash yolks.
Stir in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spoon mixture into egg centers.
Cover loosely and refrigerate.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine cranberry, mayonnaise, zucchini, orange juice and rind.
Mix dry ingredients and nuts.
Add to cranberry mixture and blend well.
Bake in lightly greased and lined with brown paper on bottom of 2 small loaf pans at 350° about 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and turn on rack.

title: pepper bacon-wrapped pork tenderloin
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat; add mushrooms and onion and saute 8 minutes or until tender. Stir in pecans and set aside. Place pork between 2 sheets of plastic wrap. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with salt and ground pepper. Spread mushroom mixture evenly on 1 side of each tenderloin, leaving a 1/4-inch border. Roll up jellyroll fashion, starting with 1 long end. Wrap 4 bacon slices around each tenderloin and secure with wooden picks. Place seam sides down on a lightly greased rack in a roasting pan. Rub evenly with sugar and cracked pepper. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 400° for 15 minutes or until a meat thermometer registers 160°.

title: jiffy jerky
directions: You will also need a Brinkmann meat smoker.

title: shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Mix ingredients until soft dough forms. Gently smooth into ungreased round pan, 8 x 11 1/2 or a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch krispies
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: rice beef
directions: Heat oil and add onions.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add meat and cook until light brown.
Add rice and other ingredients.
Stir well. Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes or until rice is cooked. Stir occasionally so that mixture does not stick.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mixing until thoroughly moistened.
Pack into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan lined with waxed paper. Cover tightly and chill at least 48 hours before slicing.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil. Remove from heat; add gelatin and stir to dissolve. Add buttermilk and mix well. Cool to room temperature. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Cut into 12 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over the raisins. Add the soda.
Cool. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the eggs and buttermilk.
Fold into the flour, salt, nuts, All-Bran and bran flakes.
Mix all only until moist. Store in covered bowl in refrigerator until ready to bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased muffin tins. Batter will keep in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cook together milk and flour into a thick sauce.
While sauce is cooling, cream shortening (not butter) with sugar to a smooth consistency.
Add cooled sauce to this mixture. Flavor with vanilla and beat until the mixture is double in bulk. Spread on cooled cake and refrigerator.
Frost with Ho Ho Chocolate Frosting.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix ingredients with fork.
Flour board.
Knead dough on floured surface until right texture (not sticky or too dry).
This is where more flour may be added.
Roll out dough with floured rolling pin, adding flour as you go so it doesn't stick to board or pin.
Roll as thin as possible, will be circle 16 to 18-inches. Air dry just a little while, if needed.
Start at edge and roll up before it gets crackly.
Cut into thin strips, then spread strips out flat to dry.
Store in food bags in refrigerator.
Cook in boiling water, test for doneness.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and margarine.
Add eggs; beat smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pie pan.
Top with other pastry.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Cream the oil, sugar, eggs and molasses in a large bowl.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Sift the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture; mix well. Refrigerate for several hours. Take 1 teaspoon dough and roll into a hot dog shape.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: basil chicken and pasta
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Saute chicken in vegetable oil until meat turns white.
Add mushrooms and basil, cook until mushrooms are tender.
Add pasta sauce and simmer until heated through.
Cook fettuccine according to directions.
Top fettuccine with basil chicken sauce.
Garnish with Romano cheese.
Serves 4.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Meat Sauce:
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, 6 ounces of water and 1 tablespoon of basil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain and toss with 1 tablespoon of oil.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat. Add flour and baking powder.
Beat.
Roll into strips about 1/2-inch in diameter and 2-inches long.
Dip in milk and then roll in sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to instructions on box.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put 1/4 cake batter in pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and butter with milk.
Pour melted caramel mixture over cake.
Pour remaining cake batter on top of caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: turkey-rice casserole
directions: Heat soups and milk together.
Either place instant rice in bottom of 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole and pour soup mixture over the rice or mix the rice in the soup mixture (mixing rice and soup makes rice softer).
Cut turkey in small pieces and sprinkle over this mixture.
Garnish top with buttered bread cubes or sprinkle with dry onion soup.

title: family style chicken casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients; place in a greased large Pyrex dish.
Then sprinkle the other 1/3 of stuffing mix on top. Then sprinkle some of the chicken broth over the stuffing mix or you can sprinkle water.
(Just something to make it a little bit moist.)

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetable oil.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into 1/8-inch hot oil in a large skillet.
Cook to golden brown, turn and brown other side.
Yields about 14.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning mix.
Layer next five ingredients: sour cream, taco sauce, cheese, olives and tomatoes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cook until tender.
Drain.
Beat softened cream cheese with cream in mixer.
Add hot potatoes and blend well.
Add butter and seasonings.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place saltine crackers side by side to cover foil.
Bring to a boil butter (not margarine) and sugar.
Spoon mixture over saltines and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over baked saltines.
Sprinkle chopped nuts (if desired) over melted chocolate chips.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
When hardened, break into uneven pieces and store in refrigerator.
Enjoy. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cover and cook onion and celery 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Boil and stir until cheese is melted.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Heat soup and add softened gelatin and cream cheese and blend well. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased mold. Chill well. Serve with crackers.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together and add ice.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all beans, pimentos, onions and celery.
Make dressing of vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Pour over first mixture and chill overnight.

title: dough for apple dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix in Crisco and add beaten egg and milk.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry-apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add raspberries, applesauce, apples and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Cut into 12 to 16 blocks for serving.

title: lo-cal chocolate banana pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed; pour into 9-inch pan. Slice banana over the pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl and toss with two forks for about 1 minute.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix until combined.
Spoon into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pans one minute.
Remove and put on wire rack until cool.
Makes 1 large 9 x 4-inch or two smaller ones.

title: bro. kelley's chocolate gravy
directions: Add as much milk as needed to bring to desired thickness.
Cook gravy in cast-iron skillet.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: mrs. louise moore's spoon bread
directions: Mix water, cornmeal and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, then stir in milk, eggs and butter.
Mix well.
Pour in heated, well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes, or until top is firm and well browned.
If you have any leftovers, it is good warmed with butter on top.

title: large batch bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water into large bowl with sugar, shortening and bran.
Stir until shortening is dissolved.
Add eggs, buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: grandmom b's stuffing
directions: Remove sausage from casing and fry in butter or oil.
Add celery, onion and garlic to sausage; cook approximately 1/2 hour. Beat eggs and cheese together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Stir egg mix to sausage mix and cook until eggs solidify.
If too dry, add 1/2 cup chicken broth.
If too wet, add bread crumbs or more bread cubes.

title: imperial crab casserole
directions: Beat egg.
Add mayonnaise, Old Bay seasoning and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Add crab meat carefully so as not to break up crab lumps.
Put in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: celery-rice soup
directions: Combine celery, rice, onion, salt and pepper with water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add milk and butter.
Heat until butter is melted.

title: fudge
directions: Boil until soft stage.
Set in sink of cold water and beat until you can draw a line across pan and it doesn't run.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of French fried onions. Spoon mixture into casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops on top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: peach plum pie
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, peaches, plums and lemon juice.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Roll half of pastry and line 9-inch pie pan. Use rest for top crust or lattice top.
Dot with butter, then put topping on.
Bake at 425° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce.
Toss gently.
Chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat; season.
Spray dish with Pam.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Layer tortillas, then add meat.
Mix soups, milk and enchilada sauce and pour over meat.
Add cheese.
Repeat more layers, if wished.
Bake at 350°.

title: spoon cornbread(do not let mix sit)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onion, chiles and cheese.
Pour half in greased baking bowl.
Top with onion, cheese and chiles. Pour over remaining mixture and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugars and oil; add beaten eggs, apples and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and blend with sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
If too dry, add more oil.

title: cherry breeze pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and then press into a 9-inch pie pan and put in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.
Mix with mixer next 4 ingredients all together for about 2 minutes.
Then, pour mixture into pie crust and put into freezer for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Take can of cherries and pour on top and then put in refrigerator for about 30 more minutes.
Then, enjoy.

title: poppy seed potatoes
directions: Combine in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and dry fruits.
Put fruits into food processor and process.
Add sugar.
Process to mix well.
Put in large Tupperware bowl.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: arroz con pollo (chicken with rice)
directions: The night before:
Cut chicken.
Rub with garlic, oregano, salt and pepper mixture.
Marinate in 3 tablespoons of oil in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix in mushrooms.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients.
Pour over rice and mushrooms. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken with biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In oven, melt butter in baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken. Place chicken, skin side down in butter.
Bake 35 minutes.
Make biscuit dough.
turn chicken, pushing pieces to one side of pan. Drop biscuit dough by spoonfuls into pan in single layer next to chicken.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until biscuits are light brown and chicken is tender.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large heavy saucepan on medium heat.
Pour off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: homemade granola
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil and honey in a saucepan.
Heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients in a large cake pan. Pour sugar mixture over dry mixture and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Cut chicken in small strips and put in butter.
Cut up green peppers and onions and put in skillet to simmer.
Cook over medium-low heat until chicken is done, about 15 minutes.
Warm tortillas in microwave and serve with chicken mixture, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: blueberry salad(sugar-free, low-fat)
directions: Drain raspberries and pineapple, reserving liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add to dissolved gelatin.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When gelatin is slightly thickened, fold in fruit. Chill until firm.

title: no fail banana bread
directions: Combine bananas, sugar, shortening and egg with Bisquick.
Put in a greased bread pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° and then at 300° until done.

title: bread dressing
directions: Cook margarine, celery and onions; add poultry seasoning, remove from heat.
Place bread in large bowl, add warm ingredients, then broth, then eggs.
Place in oven, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie(no-bake)
directions: Whip cream cheese on high until fluffy.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Mix at medium speed.
Add milk and mix until blended. Fold in the whipped topping gently and put in pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and drizzle melted chocolate over the top. Freeze until firm.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in pie shell that has been baked about 5 minutes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Mix and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serve with Fritos, etc.

title: fish almondine
directions: Cut the fish in serving pieces; fry in the butter in a heavy skillet for 10 to 15 minutes, browning both sides.
Remove to a platter and keep hot.
Add the almonds to the butter left in the skillet; saute to a golden brown.
Add flour, salt and pepper; blend thoroughly, then stir in the top milk or cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the sauce is smooth and thick.
Pour over the fish; touch up with a dash of paprika.
Serves 4.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add syrup and rum; set aside.
In large bowl combine crushed wafers and sugar.
Add chocolate mixture, mixing well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Roll in balls with powdered sugar.

title: fiesta cheese dip
directions: Microwave Instructions:
In microwave bowl, combine tomatoes and cheese.
Stir, cover and microwave 8 to 10 minutes on Medium until melted.
Stir twice during cooking.
Mix well.
Serve warm.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: grandma's frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cheese until fairly smooth.
Add pineapple, cherries, marshmallows and nutmeats.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over before mixing.
Whip the cream; mix in.
Put in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.

title: krum kake
directions: Mix together.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon on Krum Kake iron and bake at medium heat.
Turn and bake on the other side.
Roll on a wooden peg.
Makes about 50.

title: scotch-a-rue
directions: Boil brown sugar and syrup.
Off stove, add peanut butter; mix good.
Add cereal.
Pack into loaf pan (tight).
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips with 6 ounces butterscotch chips and spread on top.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Heat
to boil the sugar and syrup.
Mix all ingredients and pat into two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: mashed potato patties
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Heat pan with bacon drippings.
Drop by tablespoon and fry.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Bring to boil; let simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup and peanuts together.
Heat to boiling and boil exactly 7 minutes.
Remove from heat, add food coloring, vanilla and oleo.
Beat until color changes.
Drop onto wax paper or aluminum foil and let cool.

title: chess squares
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef brisket
directions: Using at least a tablespoon of each salt, rub into both sides of roast.
Place meat in heavy plastic Ziploc bag.
Pour half bottle of liquid smoke; Ziploc it.
Keep turned at least 4 times during 24 hour period.
Refrigerate during 24 hours.
Drain meat, place in baking dish pouring approximately 1/4 bottle Worcestershire sauce over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Slice diagonally to serve.

title: lasagna florentine(this can be prepared in advance and refrigerated)
directions: Drain
uncooked
spinach
on
paper towels.
Meanwhile, cook ground
beef
and onion in skillet until beef is browned. Add mushrooms, tomato sauce, salt, oregano, basil and pepper. Cover and
simmer 15 minutes.
Mix together spinach, 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon
salt.
Set
aside.
Combine cottage cheese and 1 egg. Mix well.
Set aside.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 15 x 13-inch cookie sheet, greased. Bake 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in a greased 3-quart casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: ham-filled party biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour until mixed.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out dough into a rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with ham.
Dust with brown sugar and dry mustard. Roll up in jelly-roll fashion.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 400°. Cut roll into 16 slices.
Place slices on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pecan tassies(from 1975 edition)
directions: First make crust by beating butter and cream cheese, then add flour.
Shape balls of dough about size of walnuts and press into ungreased small size muffin tins.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into bowl; add sugar and buttermilk, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in shortening.
Mix sifted flour, salt, and baking soda; stir into first mixture.
Allow to raise in a warm place for about 1/2 hour.
Shape as desired, brush with melted butter.
Allow to raise again on greased pans until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple-lime velvet salad
directions: Mix jello in water; stir until dissolved.
Add cheese and beat until cheese is blended.
Chill until slightly set, then add pineapple and celery.
Fold in whip cream.
Chill.
Ready to serve.

title: hobo bread
directions: Stir together the water, raisins and baking soda and let set overnight.
The next morning, preheat oven to 350° and grease 2 loaf pans.
Add the sugar, salt, cooking oil, eggs, flour and nuts to raisin mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pans, filling each pan half full.
Bake for 1 hour.
Ovens may vary, test for doneness. Cool on rack.
Very good!

title: company brunch
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Grease a 10 x 16-inch casserole dish and add croutons.
Sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs; add seasonings.
Pour mixture over croutons and cheese. Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: theresa's deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs and scoop out yolks.
Combine yolks and all other ingredients; mix well with an electric mixer.
Fill egg white halves with mixture; garnish with paprika.

title: lemon barbecued meat loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, mix well the ground beef, bread crumbs, lemon juice, minced onion, egg and seasoned salt.
Shape the mixture into 6 individual loaves.
Place in baking pan and bake 15 minutes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add to it, eggs and vanilla.
Mix separately oatmeal (which has been powderized in a blender), flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Add chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Make golf ball sized balls 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: creamy cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix by hand in a small bowl the ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in a 9 x13-inch pan. Butter crumbs and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all spices together.
Stir in salad dressing.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Stir well.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Mix sugar and baking powder and gradually add to egg whites and beat until stiff peaks form.
Grate chocolate, reserving 2 tablespoons.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Sift flour three times and set aside.
Mix together soda and sour cream and set aside.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and sour cream mixture alternately to butter mixture.
Stir in bananas and chocolate chips.
Add vanilla and salt.
Place mixture in a greased and floured loaf pan and bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 40 to 45 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
(You can use 3 baby pans, 6 x 3 1/2-inches.
Test at 35 minutes.
I would recommend this if you are planning to store or freeze part of the bread.) Serve with sweet, creamy butter.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix white cake mix with walnuts according to package directions and pour into 2 greased round layer pans.
Bake cake. Split layers when cool.
Punch holes in cake with fork.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat chocolate syrup in heavy pan over medium heat until it reaches the boiling stage.
Let it almost come up to a rolling boil.
Add vanilla and salt, then add condensed milk, stirring very rapidly as it is poured in.
Immediately reduce heat to low; continue to stir constantly until well emulsified.
Do not remove from low temperature for several minutes.
It will get thick and creamy.
Remove from heat; stir occasionally.
Keep warm.

title: mom's bake and boil cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and add baking soda, vanilla, wine, flour and ground nuts.
Grease pan and put wax paper in and grease paper.
Bake cake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is dry when testing center.
Makes 2 loaf cakes or one tube cake.
Tube cake could take longer to bake than 1 hour (1 hour 15 mintues or 1 1/2 hours).
Pat with wine before storing. Ice with white frosting.

title: sweet heart salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the sugar and pineapple with juice, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon and cherry juices.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whisk in cheese until thoroughly combined.
Stir in cherries and food coloring.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water to make 1 cup of hot chocolate.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, flour, sugar, salt and pepper; mix. Add beaten eggs to squash mixture; then add melted butter.
Drop in frying pan with hot oil; fry like pancakes.

title: cabbage parfait
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Beat mayonnaise and cold water with vinegar and salt.
Stir in the cabbage and radish.
Pour into a quart mold or individual molds.
Chill until set.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: This is baked in layers.
Fry meat, celery, mango and onion all together until brown; drain.
Add pepper and salt.
Layer as follows:
meat mixture, tomatoes, noodles (cooked as on package), peas, mushroom soup (mixed with juice from peas) and grated cheese. Bake at 350° in deep dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place in large bowl margarine, chocolate chips, nut meats and vanilla.
Place in large pan the sugar and milk.
Bring sugar and milk to boil.
Stir regularly.
Boil 13 minutes.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Beat hard.
Pour into greased, large cookie sheet or pan.

title: honey nut granola
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly stir together the oats, walnuts, oleo, honey and salt.
Spread evenly in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven, stirring occasionally until light golden brown, about 25 minutes.
At once, spread mixture onto an ungreased cookie sheet or foil to keep granola from browning further.
Cool completely.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add carrots and pineapple. Sift the dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Include nut meats.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in well-greased angel food pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: diabetic pickled beet salad
directions: Drain beets and place in medium bowl; reserve juice in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients to beet juice.
Bring juice to boil; immediately remove from heat.
Pour juice mixture over beets.
Chill; drain beets before serving.
Half cup = 1 vegetable.

title: venison jerky
directions: Combine last 8 ingredients in glass dish.
Trim off all fat from meat.
Slice into 1/8-inch pieces.
Marinate in dish overnight.
Lay strips on broiler pan.
Cook in oven on lowest temperature possible.
Crack open oven door for about 4 to 6 hours. Taste occasionally for doneness.
Cool in airtight plastic bag or jar with a tight lid.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in hot milk for 5 minutes.
Mix in butter, salt and sugar; pour over eggs.
Add vanilla and raisins, if desired, and mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Set dish in large shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° until firm, about 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: molded ambrosia
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Add oranges, pineapple and nuts and coconut.
Chill.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add yeast to
1/2 cup warm water; add other ingredients and roll out as
ordinary biscuits.
Dip in butter and bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 8 minutes.

title: onion pie nanette
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp, but not browned. Cool. Preheat oven to 350°. Stir egg yolks, cream, salt, cayenne and wine into onion. Fold beaten egg whites into onion mixture. Fill pie shell and bake 1/2 hour.
Serve hot or cold. Serves 12.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Brown and drain grease from hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Great on nacho chips.

title: phoenix hotel coffee shop's french dressing
directions: Marinate onions with sugar; blend dry ingredients and add corn oil, vinegar and marinated onion.
Beat well and blend in horseradish.
Let stand an hour.
Makes 3/4 quart.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cranberry ketchup
directions: Combine ingredients; boil rapidly until thickened.
Pour into glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: slippery snakes
directions: Pour half of apple juice into a pan.
Boil.
Add package of jello.
Mix well.
In a different bowl, mix remaining juice and Knox.
Add to hot juice.
Add ice.
Mix well.
Remove unmelted ice.
Refrigerate for approximately 15 minutes.
Place mixture in a Ziploc bag.
Cut corner of the bag.
Squeeze mixture onto wax paper in the shape of snakes.
Chill 2 hours.
Have fun.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat mix well.
In the same bowl, add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix that together well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, by hand.
Roll into log.
Roll log in coconut.
Chill;
slice.
Bake
at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add cream, stirring constantly.
Add broth according to desired thickness of soup.
Add broccoli, nutmeg and potato soup.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into serving bowls; sprinkle with finely grated Cheddar cheese.

title: oven chicken
directions: Marinate chicken and sherry overnight.
Combine other ingredients and cook, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together ingredients (except chocolate bars and pecans); spread on cookie sheet.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and spread chocolate bars over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cool 20 minutes and cut.

title: derek's favorite rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt.
Slowly add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; place in pan of water about 98°.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Turn dough out on floured board.
Divide in half.
Roll each half into 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into 12 strips.
Hold on end of strip (about 1-inch wide) and wind around to form coil.
Tuck end under.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover; let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° about 12 minutes.

title: cheese divan
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch) arrange broccoli.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: chopped pickles
directions: Grind green tomatoes, cover with water, bring to a boil and drain.
Simmer with remaining ingredients 1/2 hour.
Put in hot jars; seal.

title: bread
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar with 1 cup warm water.
Sprinkle yeast on top of water.
Scald milk and remove from heat.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and margarine; cool to lukewarm and mix with yeast mixture. Add 5 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add 2 eggs; beat until well blended.
Then add about 4 cups flour to make a dough that can be handled.
Turn out into a greased pan and turn over once to bring greased side to top.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and knead on floured board.
Shape into rolls or put in loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 400°.

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Thinly slice cucumber; sprinkle with salt; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Combine sour cream, vinegar, Tabasco, chives, dill seed and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Heat oil in heavy frying pan or Dutch oven; cook onion and garlic slowly to golden brown.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add 3 cups water, vegetables and spices and bring to a boil.
Mix flour in one cup of water and slowly stir into mixture to thicken. Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Stir in ketchup and serve.
Serves 4.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, water and salt.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place sliced onions in bottom of slow cooker.
Add chicken, seasonings, tomatoes, sauce, mushrooms and water or wine.
Cover; cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve chicken with sauce over hot buttered spaghetti, linguine or vermicelli.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat remaining ingredients together until fluffy.
Mix 2 mixtures well; roll into small balls and press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: mom's summer broth
directions: *If bone is used, add 2 tablespoons dry beans and 1 tablespoon rice.

title: chicken and cheese crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, heat cream of chicken soup, milk and 4-oz of the cheese over low heat. Meanwhile, separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Place some chicken onto the large end of each roll and top with a little cheese.
Roll up and place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture directly into the baking dish, not on top of the rolls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes, or until rolls rise slightly and are lightly browned.
Pour the remaining 1/2 of the soup mixture into the dish, laying any leftover chicken meat on top, and sprinkle with any remaining cheese.
Return to oven until rolls are browned and cheese has melted.

title: breakfast coolies(fast and easy)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May also be baked in microwave.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk with pudding, then add Cool Whip; mix well.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish with whole graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mix over crackers.
Cover with second layer of graham crackers, then pour remaining pudding mix over crackers.
Place third layer of whole graham crackers over pudding mix and spread melted frosting over layers of crackers. Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package instructions.
Let cool enough to handle.
Mix by hand all ingredients, setting aside the sauce.
Spoon cheese mixture into each shell.
Place, open shell-side down, in a baking dish, covered with sauce (about 1 1/2 cups).
Cover shells with remaining sauce and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups of the boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add the spices.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add the fruit juices and remaining 2 cups of water.
Mix well and strain. Heat again to boiling.
Serve immediately.

title: delicious ritz biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, soda and sugar.
Warm milk slowly; do not overheat.
Dissolve yeast in buttermilk.
Cut shortening into flour mixture as for biscuits.
Stir in buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Turn dough out onto floured board; knead just until smooth.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter. Brush top of each round with melted butter.
Place one biscuit on top of another, making double biscuits.
Cover; let rise about 1 hour until light and doubled.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 18 biscuits.

title: frozen fruit salad(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Mix and freeze.
Makes a big, big salad.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cook just until edges are set to get nice chewy cookies.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: hash brown delight
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Combine sour cream, soup and 1/2 cup butter.
Add salt, onion and cheese; mix well.
Add potatoes. Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan (baking dish).
Combine 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french fried egg sandwich
directions: Fry egg; toast bread slices.
Add mayonnaise.
Put egg and cheese on bread.
Put in microwave 10 seconds.
Great sandwich.

title: chip soap
directions: Caution:
Solution is caustic.
Do not touch with bare hands.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook the cider over medium heat until it boils.
Boil 15 minutes.
Peel and core the apples.
Cut into small pieces.
Add apples to boiling cider.
Cover.
Cook apples over low heat until tender, about 1 hour. Stir often.
When apples are tender, remove pot from heat.
Mash apples with a potato masher.
Stir in the honey, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Cook the apple mixture, uncovered, over low heat for 30 minutes or until thick.
Cool for at least 15 minutes, then spoon into jars.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil, add eggs one at a time, beat well after each. Add cake mix and nectar. Cook at 325° for 1 hour in greased stem pan. When cake cools turn out on plate and add the following glaze; 1/3 c. lemon juice, 1 1/2 - 2 c. powdered sugar. Heat until smooth and pour over cake while hot. Prick cake with fork before pouring glaze on cake.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: In large saucepan, cover chicken with water and boil until chicken is fully cooked.
Remove chicken from broth and debone chicken.
Place deboned chicken back in broth along with 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to a boil. Turn down to medium heat.
Cut cheese into pieces and add to mixture, stirring constantly, so the cheese doesn't scorch.
When this is melted and mixed, add package of noodles and cook until tender.

title: french vanilla custard ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add quart of milk and mix thoroughly.
Heat just to boiling.
Beat egg yolks; add 1 cup hot mixture.
Add egg mixture to milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, Pet milk and cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into milk mixture.
Pour into a 1-gallon freezer container.
Add remaining milk to fill can 3/4 full. Freeze as any ice cream.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Beat in cocoa and flour. Add vanilla and combine. Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Peel and scrub potatoes clean.
Cut into thin slices halfway through the potatoes.
Place into baking dish.
Sprinkle salt, butter and onions on top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 425°.
Remove and sprinkle cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 7 to 10 minutes to golden brown.

title: baked garlic potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice them like French fries.
Lay in bottom of pan.
Slice onion and spread slices over potatoes like little onion rings.
Take butter, slice thin and layer over top of the potatoes and onions.
Take garlic salt and sprinkle over the ingredients pretty heavily.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Put olive oil in frying pan and heat on medium to medium-high. Add pork chops and crushed rosemary.
Cook until done (nicely browned on outside).

title: party punch
directions: Mix all juices and add Kool-Aid with 1 gallon water and syrup. Chill.
When serving, add ginger ale.
You may add sherbet also.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix contents.
Marinate overnight.
Bake in oven for 3 to 5 hours with oven door slightly ajar to let out moisture.
Have oven at 200°.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tight jar in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat the sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Add 1 cup of melted morsels; mix well.
Add the flour, oats, baking powder, 1 cup morsels and the chopped nuts.
Mix well; spread into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: quick pancakes
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth.
For each pancake, pour batter onto hot, greased griddle.
Turn when top is bubbly and beginning to dry; brown other side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: japanese stew
directions: Stew chicken breasts.
When chicken is done, cut into 1 inch cubes.
Saute onions.
Add chicken, sauteed onions, carrots and potatoes to "Japanese Stew mix" and cook until tender.

title: best ever zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except zucchini until well blended.
Add zucchini and stir until evenly distributed with mix.
Bake in two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans which have been well-greased at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 8 to 10 minutes.
Add and mix half and half, whipping cream, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour in 1/2 gallon whole milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Mix chicken soup, enchilada sauce and peppers.
Bring to a boil.
In large casserole dish, layer meat sauce, tortilla chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: 12 day sweet pickles
directions: *Or use pickling spices, one half bow for listed mixture (remove crushed red pepper).

title: no peep stew
directions: Place stew meat in casserole.
Add frozen mixed vegetables. Pour tomato soup over.
Bake at 250°
for 5 hours, covered.
Do not peek.

title: tex mex cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan; set aside.
Break egg into bowl and beat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: pumpkin-maple pie
directions: In large bowl, whisk pumpkin, milk, 3/4 cup maple syrup, eggs, flour, pumpkin pie spice and maple flavoring until blended.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 425° on lowest oven rack for 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° and bake for additional 40 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Cover crust with foil, if needed, to prevent excess browning.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cheeses and milk; cook until cheese melts.
Mix flour and water until smooth.
Add to milk mixture.
Add spices and bread crumbs.
Cook until thick.
Combine macaroni and sauce.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with grated cheese and more bread crumbs if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until sides are brown.

title: mom's never fail dill pickles
directions: Pack the clean cucumbers closely in a half-gallon jar. Sprinkle the chopped heads of dill through as the jar is packed. Add the salt, vinegar, garlic and spices and fill the jar with cold water.
Screw on the cover.
Leave for a few days where the jar may be shaken occasionally until the salt has dissolved.
Do not use for 2 weeks.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form small balls and brown in oil. Remove from pan.

title: grace sain's enchilada sauce
directions: Cover bottom of large iron skillet with oil.
Add flour and brown
lightly.
Add
chili
powder.
Mix and add water to make sauce.
Dip
both
sides
of corn tortillas in sauce.
In each tortilla,
add
some
onion
and cheese.
Roll and put in Pyrex baking
dish.
Top	with any remainder of cheese, onion and sauce. Bake at 300° until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Time of preparation: 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken acapula
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Spoon about 1/2 c. chicken mixture in the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in greased pan. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eve's roll cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat the eggs and combine with the sugar, oil, vanilla and orange juice.
Add flour until the mixture forms a dough.
Add baking powder.
Roll into a ball and chill one hour in refrigerator.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll out 1/3 onto a floured cloth.
Spread with jam and sprinkle on raisins, walnuts and cinnamon.
Roll into a log shape and roll onto a greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with the remaining 2/3 of dough. Sprinkle all three with cinnamon and bake for about 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form a loaf.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all in mixing bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to use.

title: pita burgers
directions: Stir together lettuce, cucumber, yogurt and sesame seed; set aside.
Combine meat, onion, garlic, salt, oregano, basil and rosemary; mix well.
Shape into 6 thin patties, each 5 inches in diameter.
Grill over medium coals (or broil 3 to 4 inches from heat source), to desired doneness, turning once (allow about 5 minutes total cooking time for medium).
Split bread to make a pocket; place cooked meat patty inside.
Spoon in lettuce mixture. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs, spices and then the potatoes, flour and milk, a little at a time.
Add nuts and currants.
Roll or drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl or pan.
Combine sugar, syrup, water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Add cream of tartar; boil to soft ball stage (250°).
Remove from fire.
Add soda, oleo and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; stir and form into balls.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In small bowl, beat on medium speed the cheese, mayonnaise, onion and ketchup until fluffy.
Add shrimp and beat on low speed. Refrigerate.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: biscuits
directions: Knead in a little flour before rolling out.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: crab salad or shrimp
directions: Mix and add 2 packages Equal to sweeten.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Stir sugar, syrup, milk and butter over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cut chocolate into small pieces and stir in with others.
Boil slowly.
Add vanilla.
Pour candy into lightly buttered tins.
When firm, about 3 hours later, put on a board and cut into 3/4-inch squares.

title: chicken filling
directions: Cook chicken, bone and dice. Combine chicken, all but 1 c. shredded cheese, green chilies, salt and pepper. Mix well. Place a large spoonful of mixture on each crepe; roll up. Arrange filled, rolled crepes in shallow baking dish (9 X 13) and top with remaining cheese. Pour cream over all. Cook at 325 degrees for 20-30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: three cheese chicken lasagna
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add American cheese, chicken soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
If too thick, thin with chicken stock.
Layer noodles, chicken, chicken sauce and cottage cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, combine the peanut butter, corn syrup, brown sugar and white sugar.
Cook stirring occasionally until smooth.
Remove from heat and quickly mix in the cornflakes, chocolate chips and peanuts until evenly coated. Press the entire mixture gently into a buttered 9x13 inch baking dish.
Allow to cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and shape into balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt the last 3 ingredients in a double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls into the mixture (use toothpicks and cover 3/4 of the way).
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 100 to 150.
(Can make 1/2 recipe.)

title: peppy-mex popcorn snack
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In a large bowl combine popcorn, pretzels and corn twists.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt margarine; stir in lemon pepper, oregano, chili powder, garlic powder and onion powder.
Pour magarine mixture over popcorn; stir gently to coat.
Spread mixture in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once during baking.
Makes 11 cups.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart bottle and shake vigorously.

title: lentil rice salad
directions: Cook lentils and drain.
Cook rice according to package directions and drain.
Mix lentils and rice.
Add all other ingredients and toss.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours before serving.
Serve on a bed of greens or as a side dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine flaked fish with crushed potato chips.
Add soup diluted with milk.
Bake in casserole until brown on top in 350° oven.

title: mrs. debbee's christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in saucepan, add food coloring. Quickly mix in corn flakes.
Spoon out on wax paper or shape into wreaths.
Use red hots for holly.

title: orange chicken salad
directions: *If using uncooked chicken, spray saute pan with oil and brown the chicken.
Add orange juice and peel.
Cover pan and simmer on low heat about 5 minutes, until chicken is cooked.
Cool and add to salad with juice.
If using cooked chicken, add the orange juice and peel to dressing.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix cream cheese with mixer.
Drain turkey or chicken and tear up with hands.
Add a few diced onions and celery.
Shape into a ball or loaf and cover with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat. Blend in brown sugar and cream.
Stirring constantly, bring to boiling and cook until sugar is completely dissolved, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°).
Gradually add the sifted confectioners sugar, beating until blended after each addition.
If necessary, continue beating until thick enough to spread.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into a 3-quart casserole and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir occasionally the first 20 minutes.
This makes a nice dish to serve at church suppers.
Can be divided after baking and half frozen for later use.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: rice and easy
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
Try different broccoli mixed vegetables for a different taste.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together several times.
Put into mixing bowl. Add eggs and salad oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat with mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and both kinds of nuts.
Finally add the bananas.
Spoon the batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn onto cooling rack.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Make jello with pineapple juice; let set until thick, but not fully set.
Cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Whip the whipping cream, then beat partially set jello and add cheese mixture and blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: sausage and sweet taters
directions: Preboil sweet taters for 15 minutes.
Peel and cut into strips.
Put in greased baking dish.
Mix sugars, butter, salt and water in saucepan for 3 minutes.
Pour over sweet taters.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Put sausage on top and bake another 30 minutes.

title: green chili
directions: Brown ground turkey.
Add cream of chicken soup, green chiles and chopped onions (saute onions in tablespoon oil first).
Heat thoroughly.
Top with grated cheese.

title: cereal candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in large bowl.
Melt white chocolate and pour over dry ingredients, stirring rapidly until they are completely covered.
Spread on wax paper until cool. Break apart and store in covered container.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break biscuits in small pieces.
Place in bag of mixture (cinnamon and sugar) until fully coated.
Preheat oven to 350°. Take a greased Bundt pan; place pecans in bottom followed by biscuits.
