Melt butter and brown sugar and pour over biscuits. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups, onion, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Tear tortillas in strips and line bottom.

title: maggie's dinner
directions: Brown beef.
Add green pepper.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together, except cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Put cheese on top; bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Prepare quick chocolate crumb crust. Heat oven to 450°.

title: strawberry angel squares
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Cut cake vertically into halves.
Freeze 1/2 for future use.
Remove crusts from other half.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and soda in a bowl.
Add water slowly and mayonnaise. Bake in a tube pan (greased and floured) for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: euba's salmon soup
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve juice. Saute onion and celery in oleo. Blend in juice and flour.
Add milk and bring to a boil. Add cauliflowerets, salmon, dill and salt. Add cheese until melted. Add parsley flakes. If not thick enough, add cornstarch mixed with water.

title: chipper perch
directions: Separate fillets and cut into 4 1/2 to 5 ounce portions.
Dip fillets in French dressing, then place skin side down in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Combine chips and cheese and sprinkle the mixture evenly over fish fillets.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven, or until fillets flake easily when tested with a fork.

title: old-fashioned potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Drain.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan.
Measure cornstarch in separate dish and gradually add hot milk until cornstarch is "soupy".
Add to remaining hot milk through strainer to avoid lumps.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper and sour cream.
Cook "low" until soup is good consistency. Serves 4.

title: tar heel slaw
directions: Shred or chop cabbage and mix all together.
This makes a large bowl of slaw.
It is especially good on pork barbecue.

title: hard rolls(rundstykker)
directions: Scald milk; add margarine and sugar and stir to blend.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour mixture over yeast in mixing bowl; stir.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and salt and mix thoroughly.
Turn out on baking board and divide into 20 pieces.
Shape each piece into smooth roll and place on baking sheet.
Let rise about 30 minutes. Brush with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix and shape into a ball. Refrigerate.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
Heat pears, sugar and lemon juice until very warm.
Pour over melted butter.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk until well blended and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cool whip or evaporated milk.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: lucy's rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups broth. Saute onions and peppers in butter. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Combine tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add drained peas, mushrooms, chopped chicken, onions and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole and bake until brown and bubbly.

title: spanish rice
directions: Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Stir in all ingredients except tomatoes and green peppers.
Cover, removed from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir with fork until blended. Add remaining ingredients and let stand about 10 minutes.
(Rice will thicken upon standing.) Serves 8.

title: bro. gregg's soup
directions: Put all ingredient in a crock-pot and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add salt, celery and pepper. When onion and celery are tender, add mashed potatoes and stir in the hot milk. Simmer slowly for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with crescent rolls.
Press in the separations.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.
Mix yogurt, cream cheese and flavoring until smooth, spread over crust.
Cover with vegetable toppings and Cheddar cheese.

title: czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually add flour.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Pat down 1/2 of batter into 8-inch greased pan.
Spread filling over first half of dough.
Cover filling with remainder of dough.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Cut into 36 squares. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Can be used with all flavors of Baker brand fillings.

title: moist and delicious prune cake
directions: Mix prunes, orange juice and rind in small bowl.
Next beat in eggs, sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Last add prune juice and cut up prunes and orange juice and rind.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with seven minute frosting.

title: outrageous chicken salad(my favorite)
directions: Mix chicken, celery and grapes with salad dressing.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix crackers, almonds and 3/4 stick margarine together; set aside.
Saute
onion,
bell pepper and celery in butter or margarine on
top of stove until tender.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Pour
into
large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread(diabetic)
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix with nuts.
Combine eggs, applesauce and margarine.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, French vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Blend cream cheese mixture and vanilla pudding mixture together.
Layer in 9-inch flowerpot cookie crumbs, cream cheese-vanilla pudding mixture, cookie crumbs, etc.
Garnish with gummy bears.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and spread in a well-greased casserole.
Spread with topping mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water and 1/2 stick margarine; drain and cool. Save the broth; pull meat into bite size pieces.
In separate bowls, put celery soup and chicken soup.
Add broth equally to each soup.
In saucepan, melt stick of margarine and add stuffing mix.
In large casserole dish, place a layer of stuffing, then a layer of chicken, then a layer of celery soup, a layer of chicken soup and another layer of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Cook first seven ingredients together and let come to a boil but do not boil.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan (batter will be thin).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for aluminum pan, or 325° for 25 minutes in glass pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix sugar and flour; stir into melted butter.
Stir in milk, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in corn.
Pour mixture into 2-quart buttered casserole or two 1-quart baking dishes.
Bake in oven until top is golden brown and center is set, about 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix together in bowl by hand.
Fill paper cupcake shells 2/3 full.
Push in 1 miniature peanut butter cup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (closer to 30 minutes).

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt one stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Line bottom of 3 x 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and remaining margarine and beat for 15 minutes. Pour over crumbs.
Slice bananas and place over mixture.
Spread on pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and top with cherries.

title: morris spinach dip
directions: Squeeze the spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with Bugles or Fritos.
Enjoy!

title: crab hor d'oeuvres
directions: Soften the gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Heat soup; stir in the gelatin.
Cool slightly, then combine with remaining ingredients.
Place in mold and chill overnight.
Remove from mold and garnish with watercress.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: shortbread
directions: Soften butter and add sugar and egg yolks; mix well.
Add flour until all is worked in.
Add finely chopped nuts.
Place dough down until 1/4-inch deep on a cookie sheet and score dough with a fork.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 325°
oven.
Cut into squares while hot and let cool in the pan.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine milk and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Set aside.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together in bowl.
Pour into egg mixture; blend well.
Add additional flour to make thick batter.
Fill 9-inch skillet 2/3 full with oil or use deep fryer. Pour batter into 1/2-inch funnel.
Drizzle batter from funnel into hot oil.
Let brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat,
garlic and onion.	Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with 6 tortillas.
Add meat on top.
Cover with 6 more tortillas. Add chicken
soup
mixed
with milk.
Cover with cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
A very easy tasty dish!

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef with salts, pepper and onion.
Add tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and onion and mix with cooked noodles.
Place 1/2 noodle mixture in oblong casserole dish; cover with meat sauce, then with rest of noodles. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown.

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's stuffed bell peppers
directions: At the `stemmed end' of the pepper, cut a large circle to remove stem, all seeds and excess pepper as well as leaving a large enough opening to stuff the pepper.
Place in a pot of boiling water for approximately 2 minutes.
Remove peppers from water and drain. Cook meat, onion and celery together until thoroughly cooked and meat is crumbly.
Combine meat mixture with cooked rice, salt and pepper, to taste.
Stuff the cooked peppers with the meat/rice mixture.
Stand the peppers, open end UP, in a casserole dish. Spoon tomato sauce on each.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes, until peppers are tender.

title: nibblin' fish snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine popcorn, fish shape crackers, cereal, pretzel sticks, oyster crackers, nuts, salad dressing mix and dill weed.
Stir together until thoroughly combined.
Drizzle with oil and mix until well coated.
Store in an airtight container for up to one week.
Makes about 12 cups mix.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Boil raisins until practically dry. Add Crisco. Dissolve soda in 1 cup of water. Add sugar. Sift all dry ingredients together; add to mix. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 2 hours at 325°.

title: hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Thaw hash browns for 45 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix sour cream, potato soup, onions, cheddar cheese, salt, and pepper.
Add hash browns and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cook at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift in a bowl (twice).
Beat egg and add sugar.
To the flour mixture, add all ingredients (except raisins and nuts).
Stir well.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto an oiled cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: lazy style baked beans
directions: Place beans in a casserole.
Add brown sugar, catsup, bacon and seasonings; mix lightly.
Bury onion in mixture.
Cover; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover the last half hour of baking. Remove onion.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Cook apples until done.
Add raisins, nuts and 1/2 sugar; cream remaining sugar and eggs.
Add melted butter and spices.
Sift dry ingredients and add last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf or Bundt pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, milk, margarine, eggs and flavoring. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with topping and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: baby ruth drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Drop by half teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: crack t-cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add yolks and vanilla.
Sift together baking soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: hot dr. pepper
directions: Place Dr. Pepper in saucepan and heat just to boiling point. Do not boil.
Serve in mugs to which 1 slice of fruit has been added.
Delicious cold weather drink.

title: baby wipes
directions: Cut paper towels in half.
Place 1 half in container with lid. (The square 11-cup container from Tupperware works well.)
Save the other half of paper towels for another time.
Combine water, baby bath and oil and pour over paper towels.
Place lid on container and shake.
Remove cardboard "tube" from center of towels and pull first towel up from center.
They work great!

title: people chow
directions: In microwave, melt chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal and stir until all covered.
Dump the powdered sugar in clean brown bag; pour in cereal mixture and shake until coated.
Store in a tight container.

title: american lemonade(microwave)
directions: Mix together water, lemon juice, wine and syrup in a 1-cup measure or tea cup.
Cook 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Makes 1 serving.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Crumble yeast in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water.
Add well-beaten egg.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat well.
Add melted shortening and mix in remaining flour, kneading last.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and cover tightly.
Put in refrigerator.
Remove desired amount and shape into rolls.
These may also be used before they are refrigerated.

title: old fashioned sweet potato cobbler
directions: *1 1/2 stick butter and 1 1/2 stick margarine.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes in a baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onion, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes.
Mix lightly. Serve warm or chilled.

title: sunday eggs and ham
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk. Melt butter in frying pan. Scramble eggs. Place eggs in 9 x 13 pan. Add ham. Layer mushrooms. Heat mushroom soup and a little water on stove. Spread over mushrooms in pan. Add cheese on top. Bake at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: apple cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: frank's deli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl, then pour on the dressing.
Toss well, chill and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onions, peppers, and bacon until onions are clear. Mix ingredients together and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: new orleans style baked beans
directions: Wash beans and add 4 cups water.
Cover; bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.
Add 1 cup water and salt.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Drain liquid and save. Pour beans into a greased casserole or bean pot.
Blend chili sauce, sugar, molasses, mustard, lemon juice and pepper with 1 1/4 cups liquid saved.
Cut 3 strips bacon and brown.
Add to sauce mixture and pour over beans.
Add onion; top with remaining bacon and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cajun chicken stew
directions: In Dutch oven, make roux, using cooking oil and flour. Add chicken and cook over medium heat until brown. Add all the rest of ingredients. Cover and simmer over low heat for 60 minutes, adding water to keep meat from sticking. Season to taste. Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: christmas fruitcake muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, stir together the egg, milk and butter, then stir them into the dry ingredients to make a lumpy batter.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Spoon the batter into greased muffin cups, filling them about two-thirds full.
Bake until well risen, golden and a thin wooden toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in a large bowl and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Lightly spoon flour into a dry measuring cup; level with a knife.
Place flour in large pot, gradually add milk, stirring with a whisk until blended.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper and bacon.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated (do not boil).

title: chicken spaghetti casserole(pasta con pollo ed funghi)
directions: Chop
celery, bell pepper and onions.
Slice mushrooms. Saute vegetables in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Stir in soup and chicken, mixing
well.
Set
aside
cup cheese and add 2 remaining cups to veggies and chicken.
Stir until all cheese is melted.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add strawberries, juice and all.
Mix well.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze in a 15 x 9-inch pan.
This recipe can easily be halved.

title: jaumazzeta
directions: Salt and brown ground round in skillet with a little oil. Reduce heat.
Add onion, green pepper, corn, tomatoes, mushrooms and olives.
Cook noodles while mixture is simmering, then add noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes, until brown.
Serves 6.

title: steak waterfield
directions: Brown steak and garlic in olive oil in a heavy skillet.
In second skillet, saute bell peppers and onions.
When vegetables are tender, add mushrooms, seasonings and minced garlic.
Add vegetables to beef and add red wine.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes, then add curry and simmer for another hour.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, onion, apricot nectar, sugar, dried apricots, cider or vinegar, dry mustard, salt and red pepper in a 3-quart or larger slow cooker. Add pork; spoon some of the cranberry mixture over the top. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or until pork is tender. Remove pork to cutting board and slice. Spoon fat off sauce; serve with pork.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat with onions in large skillet; drain.
Spread beef and onions on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add layer of green beans or peas and carrots.
Make enough mashed potatoes, fresh or instant, to cover top of casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are nicely browned.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Stir ingredients together. Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange the Tater Tots on top to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 3 hours or until set. Top with desired amount of cherry pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Ice when cool (if desired).

title: rookie reubens
directions: Cut cheese and meat slices into quarters.
For each sandwich, cover one bread slice with cheese, luncheon meat, sauerkraut and second bread slice.
Spread sandwich with margarine.
Broil on each side until lightly browned.

title: gretchen and donna's flat enchiladas
directions: History:
Most California food doesn't translate well into Ohio without the specialized ingredients available there; nevertheless, some can be adapted not only to our supermarkets, but our taste buds.
Here's a favorite from the family kitchens of Coronado, California, fitted to the shelves of Clyde Evans.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix fruit together with flour, soda, spices and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar, molasses and beaten eggs.
Stir in fruit.
Use loaf pan.
Bake in 275° oven 2 1/2 hours.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted into middle of cake comes out clean.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight in covered container.
Serve to your lucky guests with Fritos "Scoops" corn chips.
Serves 8.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chunks of chicken in water 3 minutes.
Mix soups, sour cream and 1 1/2 tablespoons poppy seed together.
Drain chicken and mix into soup mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter and crush Ritz crackers into butter and stir.
Add remaining poppy seed and stir.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes and serve over rice.

title: different fruit salad
directions: Put peach pie filling and sugar in medium-large bowl.
Cut peach slices in half.
Add pineapple tidbits with liquid.
One hour before serving, add bananas and strawberries.
Stir and let sit in refrigerator until serving time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, margarine and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped cream. Gently spoon into crust. Garnish with chocolate curls. Keep refrigerated.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan with enough water to cover. Add salt.
Cover and boil about 20 minutes.
Drain and peel. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until creamy and add sugar and blend well.
Then add melted butter and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake until firm.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix well in blender.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
May be frozen.
This is equal to one 14-ounce can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: stir 'n drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
If you use plain flour, add 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine yams, brown sugar, butter and spices.
Mix until blended.
Spoon into casserole dish (well sprayed with Pam).
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat with mixer the lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk until well mixed.
Pour in pie crusts and put in refrigerator.

title: maple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and sour cream.
Add eggs and mix with wire whip until fluffy.
Add baking powder, maple flavoring and flour.
Stir.
Last of all, dissolve soda in vinegar and add.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: rich lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light in color and add lemon juice. Blend well.
Add condensed milk and blend well.
Pour into crust.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
Drain.
In baking dish, layer
ingredients	as follows:
1/2 hamburger, 2 potatoes, carrots,
peas,
onions and potatoes, then remainder of hamburger. Salt
each
layer.
Top with soup.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat bacon drippings; add flour, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Add tomatoes and water.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Separate ground turkey in large flat pan (like an open roasting pan).
Season and mix with fingers.
Then mix in onion and garlic.
Then break eggs into turkey, add Quaker oats, catsup and tomato sauce.
Mix all together with spatula.
When well mixed, add olive oil and continue to mix with spatula until oil is absorbed.
Pack the seasoned turkey into a 9-inch loaf pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours in an open loaf pan at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 slices.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Use rolls for making the crust, using either a pizza pan or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Precook sausage; drain.
Sprinkle crumbled sausage over crust; crumble frozen hash browns over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk as you would for scrambled eggs.
Pour over hash browns.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients and pour over mushrooms. Marinate for 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Serves 5 - 6.

title: quick beef and cheese calzones
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Unroll pizza crust on cookie sheet; gently stretch to form 12-inch square.
Layer beef, onions, mushrooms and cheeses on half of crust to within 1-inch of edge.
Fold crust over filling; fold edge up and seal with fork.
Cut slits in top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is hot.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve with mustard.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well and pour over bread crumbs.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Delicious with cream.

title: corn custard pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well combined.
Bake for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together well in mixing bowl. Preheat and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour. Check middle of loaf for doneness. Let sit for 2 minutes. Slice, serve and enjoy.

title: pear-yogurt light muffins
directions: Dry ingredients can be mixed night before.
In medium bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
In a small bowl, stir together egg, yogurt, milk, oil, lemon peel and juice.
Add to dry ingredients with diced pears.
Stir until mixed.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute pepper, garlic, parsley and onions until onion is transparent in olive oil or vegetable oil.
Add ground round and cook until brown.
Add other ingredients and simmer until done. Serve over spaghetti sprinkled with sharp grated cheese.

title: break off bread
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco and let melt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients except flour.
Sift and add flour into first mixture, a little at a time.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch slices
directions: Sift the flour, baking	powder and salt together.
Cream the butter, gradually beat in
sugar.
Beat
until fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Mix well, then
stir in flour mixture.
Shape into rolls about 1 1/2 inches
in
diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and
chill 2 hours.
Cut
into
1/8-inch
slices
on
ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes until brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine cornstarch, water and sugar and stir till smooth. Combine rest of ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Double this recipe for 9x13-inch pan.

title: italian biscuit sticks with sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, water and pepperoni until dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix; gently roll dough in baking mix to coat. Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 10-inch square; cut in half.
Cut each half crosswise into about 14 (5-inch) strips.
Twist ends of strips in opposite directions.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press ends of strips to fasten.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
To serve, heat pizza sauce for dunking sticks.

title: double-up cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in tart cherry pie filling.
Pour into a 12 x 20 x 2-inch pan.
Let set. Dissolve lemon gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon gelatin.
Stir in pineapple and juice.
Add whipped cream and marshmallows to gelatin mixture.
Spread on top of cherry layer.
When set, sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: children's trail mix
directions: This recipe is great for children to make themselves.
Put equal parts of each ingredient in a small Baggie.
Children will shake the bag to mix.
Presto magic - Trail Mix!

title: barbecued pork
directions: Baking Temperature: 350° and 375°.
Baking Time: 90 minutes and 20 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts in medium size pieces.
Dredge with 1/4 cup flour. Cream butter and sugar until it is fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder.
Fold in butter-egg mixture.
Stir in extracts.
Blend in flour and nuts. Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper and grease again. Pour in pan; place in cold oven.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
When done, cool in pan on cake rack.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in dish in order.
Serves 6.

title: just for kids: dustin's devilish eggs
directions: Place eggs in a saucepan.
Add cold water 1/2-inch above top of eggs.
Cover with a lid.
Heat slowly to boiling.
Turn heat very low.
Cook 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Run cool water over eggs until cool enough to handle.
Peel eggs.
Cut each egg in half lengthwise and remove yolks.

title: reuben baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place chicken breast in a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rinse and drain the sauerkraut and place over the chicken, top with slices of cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over the cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake in oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place water and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take pot off stove; add 1 cup flour (mix well). Now, add 1 egg at a time and beat vigorously; then add the next egg.

The flour mixture should be hard to stir before you add the next egg. Continue until all 4 eggs are added. Drop a teaspoon of mixture onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; lower oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes. Pierce each puff with a fork and bake an additional 5 minutes. Makes about 24 to 30 puffs.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
In a large bowl mix corn, salt and eggs. Mix well.
Stir in sauteed mixture then add cornbread mix and milk. Mix together, pour into grated cake pan.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil on stove for 3 minutes.
After boiling, take off stove and add vanilla and peanut butter stirring until melted, then add oatmeal and stir thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: caramel pecan bars
directions: Mix
flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and oleo as pie crust, then add
teaspoon	soda in 2 tablespoons water.
Mix all together well.
Pat	into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: Break up turkey to fit 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add water, salt, poultry seasoning, bouillon cubes and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 1 hour.
Remove bones from broth; strain broth, if desired.
When cool enough to handle, cut any meat from the bones; return meat to broth.
Add celery, onion and carrots.
Cover, cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Add noodles; cook, uncovered, 15 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 10 (1 1/2-cups) servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Arrange in greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Combine soup and milk in bowl and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6-8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli cuts according to directions and drain.
Saute 1/2 cup onions and 1/2 stick butter. Add cooked broccoli, undiluted soup and grated cheese.
Mix and turn contents into a 2-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until sauce bubbles.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
It's easier to mix, then knead it, as you would bread, to spread the seasonings throughout the meat.
Pack into a glass bowl, cover and refrigerate 24 hours. Remove from the refrigerator; mix well again and refrigerate for another 24 hours.
Repeat for a total of 4 days.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown steak and onion in butter until tender. Stir in other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Add a tossed salad and rye bread for a delicious supper.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: homemade shiny bubbles
directions: *Use only Joy or Dawn.

title: beet jelly
directions: Combine beet juice, lemon juice and pectin.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar and continue boiling until it reaches the "jelly stage."
Add the Jell-O or Kool-Aid and mix well.
Pour into hot jars.
Put on lids and screw caps that have been in boiling water and seal.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Crumble crackers in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Use 1/2 of the oysters.
Then add 1/2 of the cheese.
Cover with a layer of crackers; use 1/2 of the butter.
Layer remainder of oysters.
Spread remainder of cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper. Cover top layer with crumbled crackers.
Dot on rest of butter. Pour evaporated milk and liquid from the oysters over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, heat and serve with chips.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Warm pineapple juice in double boiler. Add sugar, flour, salt and beaten eggs. Cook until thick; cool. Add pineapple, cut oranges, bananas and marshmallows into small pieces. Whip the cream. Add 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Fold into custard and pour over fruit. Add nuts and chill at least 1 1/2 hours. Delicious!

title: apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place chicken pieces in a casserole dish. Mix soup mix, dressing, and preserves together. Pour mixture over chicken.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and spices thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend in butter, 1/2 of the buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat well for 3 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk; beat well again for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Banana Icing.

title: kielbasa
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast; work together with large spoon until flour is moist.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Take out as needed.
(Can either drop them or roll biscuits.)
Roll on floured board until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Dough will keep for several weeks.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Cut fryer into serving pieces, dust with flour and brown in oil.
When chicken is lightly browned, add onion and mushrooms and cook until they are lightly browned.
Add sour cream, tomato soup and seasonings, stir until blended.
Cover and simmer for about an hour or until tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy unstuffed cabbage
directions: Remove 5 or 6 leaves of the cabbage for the top.

Chop the rest of the cabbage into small pieces, cutting the hard core out. In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, put enough water to cover it. Place the chopped cabbage on top of the water and spread it evenly.
Mix the beef, pork, rice, salt and pepper and spread over the chopped cabbage leaves.
Then place the reserved cabbage leaves on top.
Pour the fried salt pork over the top leaves. Spread the can of tomato soup over entire pan.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours or more at 350°.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Add oyster crackers to rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Spread on cookie sheets to dry (approximately 2 hours).

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill overnight.

title: cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage fine and soak 30 minutes in ice water; drain. Cover with boiling water.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda and boil 3 minutes without cover; drain.
Add the salt and cook until tender; drain.
Put in a buttered casserole and add soup.
Sprinkle with pepper and cut pieces of oleo all over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and oil; knead until it forms a smooth ball.
Let rise in a greased covered bowl in a warm place (80°) until doubled. Pat dough in greased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing dough up on sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Combine other ingredients.
Fry until brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: barbecued chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
For marinade, blend together oil, soy sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Place chicken in a single layer in a glass dish.
Sprinkle with garlic, pepper, thyme or basil leaves and whole cloves.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 4 hours, turning chicken over from time to time.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and cooking oil well. Fold in the sour cream, chocolate chips and grated chocolate. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in icebox.
Drain all the beans before mixing.

title: almond pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir. If not completely melted, continue to heat, making sure you stir every 30 seconds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes; peel when tender and cool.
Mash potatoes; add oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and spices into potato mixture.
Pour into the two pie shells.
Bake at 350° until the mixture has thickened and pie shell browned.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, Crisco, margarine, vanilla and 1/2 of the cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
Mix until smooth.
Roll out dough (small amount at a time) and cut into 2 1/2 or 3-inch circles or squares.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
As soon as you take them from the oven, poke fork holes in them.
Cool and spread ice cream between them, wrap individually with Saran Wrap and freeze.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Chop chicken breasts (with salt and cumin) in food processor. Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add chicken, broth, chilies, tomato, cumin, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Spoon 1 tablespoon mixture on tortilla chips and top with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: apple and celery salad
directions: Cover diced apples with lemon juice.
Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs; add in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pastry. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: easy french bread
directions: Soak yeast in warm water in mixing bowl for 5 minutes.
Add salt, shortening, sugar and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in remaining flour until mixture leaves sides of bowl.

title: honey-grilled duckling
directions: Remove giblets and neck from duckling; reserve for other uses. Split duckling lengthwise, using an electric knife.
Place duckling, breast side down, on a rack placed inside a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prick skin with a fork at 2-inch intervals. Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 11 minutes.
Drain off drippings.
Turn duckling, breast side up, and microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until juices run clear when thigh is pierced with fork.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add other ingredients and simmer. Serve with cheese slices, tortilla chips, Doritos, etc.

title: western bean pot
directions: Combine beans, pepper, tomatoes and seasoning mix in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.

title: dean's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add melted chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients and add, alternating with the buttermilk.
Blend well. Add vanilla and boiling water and mix well.
Pour into two prepared 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Best frosted with 7 minute frosting.

title: school made rolls
directions: Mix the first five ingredients with mixer and let stand about 15 minutes (water, yeast, sugar, salt and vegetable oil). Gradually add the last 3 ingredients (flour, dry milk and egg) to the first mixture.
Let rise until doubled its size.
Turn out on a floured board and knead.
Then roll out and cut out and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise double in size.
Bake at 350° until done, browned, through.
Recipe can be doubled for larger amounts. Also can be used for buns and bread.

title: lemon squares
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, oleo and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together and beat well until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour. Beat in flour.
Add 7-Up.
All alone beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: If using a whole chicken, cook it and
dice
the
meat. Mix all the ingredients except crushed potato chips and put in a casserole dish.
Crushed chips to be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: jello creme pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip. Mix together real well.
Put into crust and freeze.
When frozen, slice and serve frozen.

title: choco-scotch cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butterscotch and chocolate over low heat stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in chow mein noodles, nuts and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 3-4 dozen.

title: ham and cheese stromboli
directions: Unroll dough on greased cookie sheet.
Place ham to 1/2 inch from edge of dough.
Sprinkle onion, bacon and cheese on top of ham.
Roll it up jelly roll style.	Stating with long side pinch seams to seal; tuck ends under, seam side down on baking sheet. Use a sharp knife cut several 1/4 inch deep slits in
top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 26 to 30 minutes.	Cool slightly before serving but serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: basic macaroons
directions: Beat egg
whites,
cream
of
tartar
and vanilla until foamy. Add sugar	and
beat
at
high speed until stiff peaks form.
By hand,
add	coconut and nuts.
Fold in cereal.
Drop by teaspoons 1-inch
apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15
to 18	minutes
or light brown.
Yields 92 small cookies or 45 medium cookies.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Quarter tomatoes.
Soak about 6 hours in 1/4 cup salt and cover with water.
Wash and put in vinegar mixture.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Seal in jars.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Mix well and add apples and nuts.
Mixture will be thick.
Smooth out in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: apricot-orange jam
directions: In a food processor or blender, process orange chunks, apricots and nectar.
Scrape into heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in 1/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce to medium and boil gently over medium-high.
Reduce to medium and boil gently for 10 to 12 minutes, until fruit is tender.
Stir in sugar.
Reduce to medium-low and cook at slow boil for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Pour into hot jars. Cover and cool before refrigerating.

title: lasagna
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes; break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano leaves and basil leaves.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: potato slices
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cracker crumbs.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° until sides are bubbly. This will make one extra-large or two medium casseroles.

title: purple cow salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Heat this mixture and dissolve the Jell-O in the mixture. Add 1 cup of cold water; let stand in refrigerator until syrupy. Save out 1/2 cup.
Add fruit to the rest and let set until firm. Whip 1 package of Dream Whip; add to the 1/2 cup of reserved Jell-O.
Spread on top of salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
In bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf (family size)
directions: Chop or break up hamburger.
Add all ingredients in order. Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Use any type pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until brown on top.

title: chinese stir-fry a la matt
directions: In hot frying pan or wok, place 2 tablespoons oil, meat, garlic powder and onion powder.
Brown meat, adding soy sauce and flavoring package from 1 package of Ramen noodles.
Set aside. Cook both packages of Ramen noodles and set aside.
In the same hot frying pan, fry vegetables in a little oil, soy sauce and second Ramen flavoring package.
Turn veggies often.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil, debone and shred chicken.
Dip tortillas (2 to 4) into chicken water and place in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add all spices to chicken in bowl; mix.
Place mixed chicken and spices on layer of tortillas; spoon on chicken soup, Ro-Tel chilies and grated cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese on top.
All of this can be adapted to your personal taste.
I like it a little spicy myself.
Place in oven at 400° until cheese melts.
Serve on hot corn tortillas.
Great for making ahead and for large parties!

title: cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Add onions, soup, milk and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut devil's food cake
directions: Lightly grease cake pan.
Spread 1/2 bag of coconut in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Mix devil's food cake mix and pour it next.
Mix together cream cheese and confectioners sugar; pour it over cake.
Mix and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate brownies(diabetic)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with fruit. Contains per serving: 0 grams fat and 10 calories.

title: caramel apples
directions: Insert sturdy wooden skewers into stem end of apple.
Combine all ingredients into a deep 2 quart saucepan.
Cook to 246° (a little dropped into cold water forms a firm ball), stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Cool until mixture thickens slightly.
Quickly dip each apple into caramel mixture and twist until evenly and completely covered.
Drain on wax paper.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix thawed topping with jello until smooth; drain canned fruit.
Add all other ingredients including fruit; fold into topping.
Serve immediately or serve chilled.
Serves 12.
No cooking necessary.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Place meat on bottom of casserole. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Next, layer onion and carrots.
Add layer of celery, then add potatoes.
Add layer of mushrooms, if desired.
Mix soup with water; pour over vegetables. Cover; bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: broccoli and corn bake
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of water.
Drain and set aside.

title: 6 cheese tarts
directions: Cut in margarine with flour; pat down in a 6-cup muffin tin. Spread with fingers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cheese with water and spices.
Pour over baked pie crusts; bake 20 minutes more.

title: meat loaf(diabetic)
directions: Grease or spray casserole.
In layers, add sliced potatoes, sliced onions, sliced celery, small can regular or chili beans, 1/4 cup rice, 1 1/2 cups tomatoes (sliced or canned), any amount of hamburg on top and 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl. Add milk and sugar; mix well.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle with jimmies and freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift and mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir well.
Add eggs one at a time, and then add carrots.
Pour into prepared cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Mix onions, cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing with 1/2 cup each of the fresh vegetables.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine all ingredients. Double for 50 people.
It's tart.

title: chilled seafood salad shells
directions: Combine crabmeat chunks, cole slaw and mayonnaise.
Toss together until well blended.
Fill shells with crabmeat mixture. Arrange shells on bed of lettuce or other greens if desired. Chill and serve.

title: louisana green beans
directions: Cook green beans until tender.
Combine green beans, tomatoes, celery, green pepper and onion powder.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 8 servings. Contains approximately 20 calories per serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Mix dry ingredients with milk and egg.
Cook in heavy pan until thick; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until they hold a peak.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar per egg white.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until very stiff. Frost pie.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: oriental-glaze chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place chicken on rack in foil-lined broiler pan.
Bake 30 minutes. Brush chicken with reserved marinade.
Turn chicken and bake another 30 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.

title: dilled macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add all ingredients and stir well.
Chill 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: twinkies
directions: Melt white chocolate over hot water (not boiling).
Pour over remaining ingredients, drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: plum nutty conserve
directions: Pit plums; do not peel.
Finely chop or grind fruit.
Measure 4 cups into a 6 or 8-quart saucepot.
Add orange peel, juice and nuts.
Measure sugar and set aside.
Mix pectin into mixture in saucepot.
Add margarine.
Place over high heat; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in all sugar. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon. Ladle quickly into hot sterilized jars to within 1/8-inch of tops, wipe rims, cover with 2 piece lids.
Screw bands tightly.
Invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn upright.
After jars cool, check seals.
(I cover conserve with paraffin to seal.)
Jam sets slowly so allow 2 weeks.
Makes about 8 (1 cup) jars.

title: orange puffs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix and sift flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk to first mixture. Bake in buttered tins 35 minutes.
Serve with Orange Sauce.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of solid greased tube cake pan.
On top of that, put the can of cherries.
Dump box of yellow cake mix on top of the cherries.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Cut up sticks of oleo and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: donuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Stir in lukewarm milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Mix in remaining flour to make it easy to handle.
Turn dough lightly on floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in size, 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again 30 minutes.
Roll out to 3/8 inch thickness, cut with donut cutter and let rise on board until thick.
Heat oil (3 to 4 inches) to 375°.
Drop donuts into hot oil and turn donuts as they rise to the surface.
Carefully remove.
Glaze if desired.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put spaghetti in water to cool.
In a pan, put the meat, garlic salt, tenderizer and onion salt.
Cook until meat is done. Add Prego sauce and mix it with drained spaghetti.
Serve with green salad and French garlic bread.

title: knox blox
directions: With wire whisk, mix together all ingredients until gelatine and Jell-O are dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Slice in one inch squares.
Place in serving dish.
Blox will be firm enough to handle and eat with your fingers.
For extra fun, top with canned whipped cream.
Enjoy!
Sugar-free Jell-O works great.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour them into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a slow oven of 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: pears with figs
directions: Use 3
parts
pears
to
1 part figs.
Slice pears very thin. Use 1/3
cup sugar to a pint of pears.
Cover pears and sugar mix with
water and boil approximately 20 minutes.
Add figs and continue
to cook 5 minutes after mixture comes back to a boil. Seal
in pint jars.
(Should make as many pints as you have pears.)

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water with salt.
When soft, run through a stainer.
Boil together milk and onions; remove onions and add milk slowly to potatoes, mixing well with a whisk.
Melt half the butter.
Add all dry ingredients and stir until well mixed, then stir into hot soup.
Boil 1 minute, strain and add remaining butter.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
If soup is too thick, add a little more milk.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry pie filling mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Frost when cool with the following:

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool.
Remove chicken from bone. Mix flour, eggs, shortening and enough chicken broth to make a doughy substance.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Add to remaining hot chicken broth and chicken.
Cook on medium heat for about 30 minutes.
Add few drops of yellow food coloring, if desired.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix half the sugar with crackers and set aside.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in saucepan with the margarine. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for approximately 1 hour, or until carrot is tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and dressing together.
Roll in crushed pecans. Let stand at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: brenda's chicken stove top casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up. Mix together Stove Top mix and oleo. Spread 1/2 of this mixture on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1/2 of the chicken pieces. Mix sour cream and soup and spread evenly over chicken. Top with remaining chicken pieces, then the remaining Stove Top mix. Add 2/3 cup chicken broth for moistness. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade cheese ball
directions: Mix and form in a ball; roll in 1 cup crushed walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Mix in seasoning mix.
In large bowl, cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Add cheese, chips and meat mixture.
Mix together.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: In large nonstick skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown eggplant slices; set aside.

title: pineapple - carrot salad
directions: Use fork to put pineapple on paper towels to drain.
Save juice to use another time.
Wash carrots.
Put on cutting board. Shred the carrots and put into bowl.
Add the raisins and yogurt to carrots.
Stir with a rubber scraper until mixed.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture. Add oats; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and coconut. Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: barbecued sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, egg, bread crumbs and sage.
Shape into small balls and brown on all sides.
Remove any drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Add meatballs and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes a great appetizer!

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: You will need 2 buttered containers.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well and pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Serve.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil.
Drain beans and add seasonings.
Simmer several hours (3 to 4) in broth.
Add sliced sausage and continue to cook (30 to 45 minutes) until sausage is done.
Add sherry.
Cook rice.
Serve beans on rice with a dollop of sour cream.

title: orange nuts
directions: Combine nuts and orange juice in a bowl.
Cover and let stand 4 hours.
Drain and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add sugar and stir well.
Microwave on High uncovered 10 to 11 minutes or until mixture becomes partially dry.
Stir every few minutes (1 to 2 minutes).
Spread nuts on greased baking sheets and cool.
Store in covered container.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pie crust and preheat oven to 350°.
Saute bacon, onions and mushrooms until bacon is done and onions are clear. Squeeze as much water out of spinach as possible.
Add to bacon mixture and cook 3 more minutes.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, cream and cheese.
Press bacon/spinach mixture in bottom of crust.
Pour cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake approximately 45 minutes.

title: turtle pretzels
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels in water.
Dip half of each pretzel into the hot caramel.
Place on a greased sheet of foil to cool.
In a saucepan, melt chocolate and shortening over low heat. Dip caramel-coated end of pretzels into the chocolate; sprinkle with nuts.
Return to foil.
Yield:
About 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy cornmeal muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl. Sift flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt together. Beat eggs until lemon colored and thick. Stir in milk. Add to creamed mixture alternately with cornmeal mixture. Beat thoroughly.
Place in muffin tins lined with baking cups.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done. Yields 12 muffins.

title: dump cake
directions: In order above, layer and bake 30 minutes (no longer).
Make sure cake mix is dry.
Do not mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush one pack of Ritz crackers and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 stick of butter over crackers. Put shredded chicken on top of crackers.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Crush the last pack of crackers and pour over soup.
Pour remaining butter on top and cook at 375° until brown.

title: guadalupe fried catfish
directions: Divide oil between two 12-quart pots and bring up to 350° (fish in one, potatoes and onions in the other). Slice fish. Season with lime juice and seasoning mix in 1 gallon Ziploc, combined with flour and corn meal.
Drop fish in hot oil and fry until done. Season onions and fries with Tony's seasoning and fry until done.
Serves 6 to 10 people. Serve with red sauce and tartar sauce.

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Mix ingredients
together in a salad bowl.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve with AVOCADO DRESSING.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Put angel food cake in jello mold. Use fork to punch holes in cake. Pour jello over cake and refrigerate to gel.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: almond chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic powder.
Cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Add chicken to sauce.
Marinate for at least 2 hours.
In another bowl, combine flour, almonds and seasonings. Add chicken and toss.
Cook in a saucepan for 20 minutes.

title: target meat loaves
directions: Combine meat, milk, beaten egg, crumbs, celery, 2 tablespoons chopped onion, salt, garlic salt, sage and oregano; mix well. Shape about 1/3 cup meat mixture around each hard-cooked egg. Arrange loaves in baking dish.
Cook 1/4 cup onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1/4 cup water and parsley.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spoon sauce over loaves; top each with cheese triangle.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Very good.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: waffles
directions: Take a big spoon and stir it all around.
Put it in the oven. Cook it all up at 60 temperature.
Take it out of the oven with an oven thing on your hand.
Blow on it to cool it off.

title: lou's barbecued leg of lamb
directions: Broil on an outdoor grill not too fast (raise up 6-inches or more from hot coals) until medium brushing each side as you turn with marinade sauce.

title: creamy mushroom barley soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine water and beef bouillon.
Boil. Add barley and boil.
Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour until tender.
Remove barley. Separate.

title: chocolate vinegar cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients into an 8-inch baking pan.
Add the liquids and stir until smooth.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in oil or margarine.
Combine all ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, stirring until cooked through; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix, seasoned salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chiles; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them out slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with dry herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheeses and bake for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned and potatoes are soft inside.
Check with a fork.

title: chicken cutlets with green pepper vinaigrette
directions: Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken; saute until just cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to platter.
Sprinkle chicken with half the salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover to keep warm.

title: grandma vogel's rhubarb crunch
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla until clear.
Pour over the diced rhubarb.
Mix the flour, quick oats, brown sugar, melted margarine and cinnamon and pour over clear mixture and rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold.
Recipe can be cut in half and baked in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: easy pasta and bean soup
directions: Heat oil in a stockpot over medium heat; add onions, celery, carrots and garlic.
Cook and stir for 4 minutes.
Add broth, drained beans, tomatoes, oregano, basil, pepper and bay leaves. Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to medium; cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Sprinkle soup with parsley and shredded Swiss cheese.

title: bacon and eggs strata
directions: Melt butter; add dried crumbs and bacon.
Set aside.
Soak soft bread cubes in milk and drain.
Add drained milk to eggs, salt and pepper.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Scramble eggs.
Add soaked bread.
Put in 9-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Put cheese over top.
Put bacon and browned crumbs over cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 5-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
To keep from scorching, remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix until well blended and then add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: carolyn's waldorf salad
directions: Mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce bed.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: microwave brown sugar fudge
directions: Stir together in a bowl.
Cook 11 minutes without stirring. Take out and stir at once, 300 strokes or about 5 minutes.
Run microwave to be sure you've counted right.
Pour into greased pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat until thick eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and zucchini; fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions in salad oil until tender, but not browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart baking pan.
Cover. Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until rice is tender. Toss lightly with a fork before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until bubbly. Add the lemon juice.
Put the sliced apples in jar and fill with cooked sauce. Process 20 minutes in water bath.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Brown flour in cooking oil until very dark.
Add onion, red pepper, salt and pepper and saute onion.
Stir in tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: date nut bars
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk, vanilla and soda. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and add to milk mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Pour in ingredients and spread.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Cut into narrow 1 x 3-inch sticks.
Dust with powdered sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: homestead cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and egg.
Blend in dry ingredients and nuts.
Press into refrigerator tray and chill 1/2 hour in freezer or in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together the butter, 3/4 cup sugar, egg, flour, cream of tartar and soda; blend well.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased round pizza pan or cookie sheet with sides. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into shallow pan, lightly greased.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
This is good with fresh fruit.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Stir milk and egg into pudding; mix in saucepan.
Add rice, raisins and nuts.
Stir over medium heat until comes to boil. Cool 5 minutes.
Stir twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm or refrigerate.
Place plastic wrap on pudding while cooling.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in the butter until the onion begins to lightly brown.
Add the ground beef and brown until no pink remains.
Drain excess grease.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste and the spices.
Mix all ingredients together.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer for an hour and a half.

title: satin pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in glass bowl.
Cook in microwave at 50% power until smooth and blended.
(Can also be done in double boiler, if preferred.)
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into chocolate mixture.
Blend thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: crab canapes
directions: Blend butter, cheese spread, mayonnaise, garlic salt and crabmeat together.
Open muffins and spread crab mixture on muffin halves.
Cut each into quarters.
Place on cookie sheet and place under boiler until cheese bubbles.
Serve warm.
Serves 48 pieces.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown hamburger. Drain excess fat. Stir together nacho cheese soup and milk. Add to browned meat. Stir in drained corn. Pour into a casserole or baking dish sprayed with cooking oil. Cover meat mixture with Tater Tots. Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven until bubbly and browned on top, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: campfire beans
directions: In a large bowl, mix all non-meat and non-bean ingredients. Add cooked beef, bacon and bratwurst. Stir in beans. Pour in two 2-quart casserole dishes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven roasted vegetables pizza(yield  one 12-inch pizza)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In a large baking dish, combine the eggplant, the onions, mushrooms and yellow peppers.
In a cup, mix oil, vinegar, dried thyme and black pepper.
Drizzle over the vegetables and toss to mix well.
Bake for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except potato chips, cheese and almonds.
Place in a large casserole and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Top with cheese, chips and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: andrea's holiday mix
directions: Measure each item; place in container.
Serve for appetizers or snacks.
Place in an airtight container to store.

title: nut horns
directions: Cream oleo and ice cream.
Add flour and blend thoroughly. Work with mixture until you can form a loaf of bread.
Divide loaf into 4 sections.
Wrap with wax paper and place in refrigerator. Chill.

title: gardener's salsa
directions: In an enameled or stainless steel saucepan, combine tomatoes with vinegar.
Cover and cook until tomatoes are soft, about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Puree briefly in batches in blender or food processor; tomatoes should be slightly chunky. Return tomatoes to saucepan and add all peppers and onions.
Simmer until salsa thickens, about one hour.
Add salt to taste.
Ladle hot salsa into clean hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Adjust lids and process in water bath canner for 15 minutes.
Check seals after 12 hours.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Makes 8 pints.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Put zucchini, pineapple and sugar sure jell in pan and stir together.
Then turn on heat and bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Skim off foam and put into hot jars and seal.

title: spanish hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain fat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper, if desired.
Add tomatoes, tomato
sauce, carrots, mushrooms, onion, olives and sugar.
Stir in water and wine.
Cover; simmer 45 to 50 minutes, until carrots are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle individual servings with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: welborn chicken basting
directions: Mix ingredients and baste chicken while baking or can be used for skillet chicken also.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set.
Marinate overnight.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Use 4 cups of any of the listed ingredients, choosing at least 1 cup of cheese.
Spread into lightly greased 10-inch pie plate. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: quick pasta and bean soup
directions: Heat oil in stockpot until hot.
Add yellow onion, celery, green onion, carrots and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until hot, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add broth, beans, tomatoes, potatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes or until macaroni and vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Spoon into bowls and sprinkle with Swiss cheese and parsley.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into pieces.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Saute onion in butter.
Add pimentos, onion, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix all together with mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese during last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: watergate salad ii
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple in a bowl.
Mix up good.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.
Eat!

title: always tender beef roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in oil.
Drain.
Combine water, bouillon, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, onion, salt and pepper. Pour over the roast.
Add bay leaves.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours, or until tender.
Remove roast.
Combine flour and water. Stir into pan juices.
Bring to boil.
Stir until thickened. Remove bay leaves before making gravy.

title: superb meat loaf(diet)
directions: If possible, put vegetables through blender.
Combine with ground beef, tomato juice and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Immediately pour
off all liquid.
Cool meat loaf before slicing.

title: sangria spritzer
directions: In tea pot, pour boiling water over tea bags.
Cover and brew for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and cool slightly.
In punch bowl, combine tea, juice, wine and concentrates.
Chill.
Before serving, add club soda.
Serve with ice and garnish with lemon and apple slices.
Makes 20 servings.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Layer ingredients in Pyrex bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Bake 5 hours in 250° oven.

title: first church swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread in cold water, then squeeze out excess.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix meat, onion and seasonings in a bowl.
Add the bread.
Blend together.
Make meat balls by rolling between palms of your hands.
Brown balls in oil in a frying pan.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with gravy and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: buttery lace cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and flour. Spoon batter by tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart onto aluminum foil-lined or parchment paper-lined baking sheets, making 3 cookies at a time. Spread batter into circles. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly brown. (Cookies will spread during baking.) Remove from oven; let cool about 1 minute. When cookies hold their shape and are cool enough to touch, quickly lift with metal spatula. Flip cookies and roll around the end of a wooden spoon. Let cool completely. (If baked cookies become too crisp to roll, reheat for 30 seconds.) Store in airtight container for up to 1 week. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: stove top franks and beans
directions: Place oleo in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Cook hot dogs until lightly browned and onion is tender.
Remove 5 pieces of hot dog for garnish.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Place mixture in a medium casserole dish and garnish with reserved hot dog pieces.
Yields 6 cups or 8 servings.

title: banana bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then flour and soda.
Add nuts.
Place in greased bread pan. Bake for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more orange juice if needed to moisten mixture.
Pack in a pan and add more orange juice to top.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: egg custard
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Will make 2 small pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Combine dry ingredients, then add applesauce, milk, sugar, oil, and egg.
Mix until moist and place in lined muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Fry ground
beef,
chopped
onions and pepper in butter until slightly
browned.
Add
canned tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, chopped garlic, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 to 3
hours.
If desired,
cook,
package
and
freeze.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms
directions: Shake chicken breasts in paper bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat until medium brown.
Drain off all fat. Add 3/4 cup hot water and simmer in closed skillet for 45 minutes. Cover chicken breasts with mushrooms and heat until piping hot.

title: chocolate cookie ice cream pie(a family favorite)
directions: Mix cookies with oleo. Press in bottom of a 12-inch pie carrier. Spread ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour topping over ice cream. Spread Cool Whip. Garnish with pecans.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and soda.
Combine margarine, cocoa, water, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; pour over dry ingredients and mix by hand (not mixer).
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore(4 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into individual pieces.
Saute chicken pieces until golden brown in 1/4 cup olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover the chicken.
Simmer it for 1 hour.
