Remove the cover to permit the sauce to reduce somewhat.
Cook the chicken until tender.
Serve with boiled spaghetti.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Let cool and take off bone.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix in a baking dish.
Put chicken over it.
Mix together soups with 2 cans chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer; low speed.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 375° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and egg.
Add to dry ingredients and mix, then add corn.
In large frypan with hot oil, pour small amounts of mixture (small cake pan size) and fry until golden brown.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Boil sugar and
milk for one minute.
Add coconut.
Mix and spread on cake.

title: broccoli-cheese potato topper
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and mustard.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir; add broccoli and microwave 1 minute.
Spoon over split baked potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Best if refrigerated overnight.
Good with raw vegetables.

title: divinity
directions: Cook water, syrup and sugar to a soft ball.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry, and pour the hot mixture over them and beat. When the mixture will begin to stand in a peak, add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoon on was paper.
(Easier to handle 1/2 batch.)

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a flat baking dish (6 x 11-inch) and place in 300° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender and pudding is thick and creamy, not dry.
Stir every 20 minutes with a fork, turning under the brown top.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 5.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
(If blender is not heavy-duty, use mixer.)
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: commercial icing
directions: Cook
milk, flour and salt.
When milk mixture has been cooked (thickened very thick) beat it up well.
Cool thoroughly.
Add sugar,
shortening,
vanilla and maple flavoring for the Chocolate Mocha-Dot Cake.
Cover the cake and center with icing and arrange chocolate chips on top.
Serve cake chilled.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add turkey and brown well.
Add mushrooms and sauce.
Stir occasionally until hot through and through. Spoon mixture into peppers and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until peppers are tender when pierced with a fork. Serve over rice.
(May also be cooked in steamer.)

title: christmas morning egg bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 4 to 5 slices French bread, cut off crust.
Then layer cooked sausage and turkey, pork or beef. Then layer 2 cups grated cheese.
Then 2 cups of sliced mushrooms. Blend 5 eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over cheese layer. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese pennies
directions: **Pasteurized processed cheese spread with bacon or garlic may also be used.

title: peanut pudding torte
directions: Blend flour and butter. Add chopped nuts. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Cream peanut butter and cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and mix well. Add Cool Whip. Spread over first layer. Mix pudding and milk well. Spread over cream cheese layer. Layer top with additional Cool Whip. Shred 1 Hershey bar over the top. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup chopped peanuts. Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mint julep(a southern tradition)
directions: Place 6 mint leaves in a tall 12 ounce glass.
Add simple syrup.
Muddle mint leaves.
Add 1 ounce bourbon.
Fill glass with ice (crushed).
Add remaining.
Stir.
Garnish with mint sprig. You may use green food coloring, 1 to 2 drops.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, spinach and water chestnuts. Add soup mix; stir all together.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Slice top off bread.
Hollow out center.
Put dip in bread for serving.
Use bread from center for dipping, along with vegetables, crackers, etc.

title: salad(chicken or turkey)
directions: Spread out slivered almonds in flat pan.
Place in 250° oven for about 10 minutes, or until brown.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each one. Blend in milk, spices, vinegar, nuts and vanilla.
Boil raisins about 5 minutes.
Drain and add all to pie mixture.
Pour into 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pie is firm.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in oil in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain mixed vegetables, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup liquid.
Combine all ingredients, except potato chips, in 4-quart casserole.
Top
with potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: meg's munchies
directions: Mix.
Spread on party rye.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time until right consistency for spreading.

title: mexican chicken corn chowder
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
In a Dutch over, brown chicken, onion and garlic in butter until chicken is no longer pink.
Dissolve the bouillon in hot water.
Add to pan along with cumin, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cream, cheese, corn, chilies, and hot pepper sauce. Cook and stir over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Stir in tomato.
Serve immediately; garnish with cilantro if desired. Yield: 6-8 servings (2 quarts).

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In large glass container, put cucumbers and onions.
Mix first four ingredients until well blended.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally.
Ready to eat in 24 hours.

title: chocolate lovers' torte
directions: Blend flour, sugar, nuts and melted butter.
Pat into a 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: lemon jello dessert
directions: Mix together the jello, sugar, water, lemon juice and grated rind.
When about thick, beat until foamy.
Whip one can of Borden ice cold milk.
When thick and creamy, fold in whipped jello. Break 1 pound of wafers into small pieces.
Line a shallow baking pan with waxed paper.
Spread the bottom with the wafer crumbs, then cover with the gelatin.
Add a layer of crumbs to the top. Set in the refrigerator until firm.
Cut in squares to serve. Serves 12.

title: amaretto fruit dip
directions: Cook pudding with milk. Let cool.
Blend in Amaretto and Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix the margarine, onion, prepared mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together.
Spread both sides of split dinner rolls.
Fill with ham and cheese slices.
Put back into foil pan the dinner rolls came in and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: curried turkeywiches
directions: Combine turkey, apple, celery, onion and parsley. Combine mayonnaise, curry, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir into turkey mixture. Spread one side of each toast slice with margarine. Arrange on baking sheet, margarine side up.
Divide and spoon turkey mixture on toast.
Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until heated.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: meat pie
directions: Saute onion; add beef and brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soup (enough to be rather wet).
Pat into pie shell.
Top with crust.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Combine everything, except the marshmallows, and place in a buttered casserole.
Press the marshmallows into the potatoes. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Immerse in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Pour 1 cup of spaghetti sauce into bottom of a shallow baking dish; set aside.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Combine eggs, sugar and cheese.
Pour over crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Cool.
Cover with blueberry pie filling and lemon juice.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix flour and milk in small pan.
Cook until thick, then set aside to cool.
In large bowl, mix sugar, Crisco, 1/2 cup oleo and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add cooked mixture and beat 10 minutes. Spread over cake and refrigerate.
Melt and cool 1/2 cup oleo. Beat the egg, chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla together.
Then add oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix well, then pour over cake and refrigerate.

title: individual cherry cheesecakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liner in muffin tin.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and extracts until smooth. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Spoon pie filling on each serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken parmigiana with spinach noodles
directions: Combine crackers, 3/4 ounce Parmesan and black pepper.

Dip chicken breast into egg; dredge in cracker mixture to coat. Combine 2 teaspoons margarine and 1 teaspoon corn oil in skillet. Add chicken; cook until slightly browned (approximately 1 to 2 minutes on each side).
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: chili verde
directions: Cut pork 1/2 inch
square and with pork bones, fry over heat until brown and meat is slightly dry.
Pour off all but 4 to 5 tablespoons grease.
Use colander.	Chop tomatoes coarsely. Combine tomatoes,
sauce,
garlic,	hot
water,
pork and bones. Bring to boil
and	boil
20 minutes.
Add spices, hot peppers and chili
strips.
Boil
minutes.	Cook on medium heat until desired
thickness (approximately 1 hour).	Remove bones.
Can
be made
ahead
of time and refrigerated up to 1 week or freeze 3 months.
Great!

title: cherry cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, egg yolk and vanilla in large bowl; mix until smooth.
Unroll crescent dough; set aside 2 rectangles.
Separate remaining dough into 12 triangles; arrange on greased 14-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Pat out dough with fingers to cover pan, pressing seams together to seal.
Using 3-inch biscuit cutter, cut out center of circle; discard.
Spread cream cheese mixture over dough to within 1/2 inch of edges; top with pie filling.
Pat out reserved dough with fingers to form 7x6-inch rectangle; cut lengthwise into 12 strips.
Twist strips and place in spoke-like fashion over filling.
Press ends of dough together to seal at both center and outer edges.
Brush strips with lightly beaten egg white.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden brown; cool.

title: grilled pork with vidalia onion gravy
directions: Season Chops and grill.
In a medium sauce pan, melt the Butter.
Add the Onions and cook until just soft.
Sprinkle on the Flour and cook for three minutes.
Slowly whisk in the Milk and Broth.
Reduce to a simmer and cook 20 minutes.
Season.
Serve warm over the Pork.
Serves 2.

title: old fashioned chicken soup
directions: Wash cut up chicken.
Put into a pot of cold water.
When water boils, skim off some fat on top.
Add ingredients.
Boil macaroni separately and then add to soup.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mash crackers into crumbs.
Put fruit and nuts in crumbs. Take sweetened condensed milk and marshmallows and put in a double boiler and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over fruit and nuts and mix well.
Mold in glass loaf dish or cracker box. Refrigerate.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 8 weeks.

title: crawfish etouffee("the real thing")
directions: Mince onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes or until vegetables are golden brown.
Stir in tablespoon of flour.
Add crawfish tails with fat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add one cup of hot water according to desired thickness of gravy.
Let simmer in a covered pot until tails are tender.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "spaghetti and meat sauce for 50"
directions: Brown chopped meat and add the remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Simmer and stir until thickened, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with cooked spaghetti, cooked as per directions on package.
Serves 50 people.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco sauce and enchilada sauce.
Mix soups, green chilies and onion.
Place a layer of tortillas (bite size) in baking dish.
Cover with layer of meat mixture, cheese and soup mixture. Repeat so you will have 2 layers of each. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with cheese and return to oven until melted.

title: peanut brittle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add brown sugar to butter.
Cream well.
Blend in 2 tablespoons beaten egg (reserve remaining egg) and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and 1/2 cup peanuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread or pat dough on 15 x 10 x 2-inch greased baking sheet.
Brush with remaining egg.
Sprinkle with remaining peanuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cut or break into pieces while warm.

title: chicken stew
directions: Clean chicken and cut into serving portions; place in stew pot and partly cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, about 2 1/2 hours.
Hard-boil 3 eggs; cut them up fine and add to stewed chicken to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water and salt.
Add chopped margarine and cheese; stir until dissolved.
Add small amount to eggs.
Return to grits; stir and mix good.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Chop enough apples to fill bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sugar and cinnamon apples to taste.
Mix together first 4 ingredients. Sprinkle on top of sugared apples.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries and eggs with a spoon.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to strawberry mixture.
Stir well.
Fold in nuts. Makes 1 big loaf and 1 small one or 3 small ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wild stir-fry chicken skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until firm and white.
Add water, contents of rice and seasoning packets, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover until water is absorbed.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: round steak louisiana
directions: Layer sweet potato slices, onion and quartered green pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Cut steak in 6 servings; pound until half original thickness.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
In skillet, quickly brown meat in hot oil.
Transfer meat to casserole, on top of sweet potato mixture; reserve drippings.
Cook garlic in reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour. Add undrained tomatoes, beef broth, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, crushed thyme, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Pour over meat and vegetables in casserole. Bake at 350° until meat and vegetables are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Occasionally spoon sauce over meat and vegetables.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Bake and let cool. Punch holes in cake (a lot of holes). Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake and let soak in a few minutes. Pour Mrs. Richardson topping over cake and let soak in a few minutes. Spread Cool Whip on top. Shave candy bar and put on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook gently 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve on pancakes, fried cornmeal mush, scrapple, as a topping for pudding, ice cream and French toast.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ziti with tuna
directions: Prepare pasta per directions on box, adding celery and onion the last 3 to 4 minutes, just to blanch.
Drain and return to pot; add butter and stir with pasta until butter is completely melted (or soften butter in microwave).
After thoroughly mixed, add drained tuna and bread crumbs and mix all together.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: This mixture fits very well in an ice cream pail and can be prepared the day before.
Make sauce the night before; the longer it sets alone, the better it gets.

title: jalapeno cheese cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done. This is a wonderful recipe.
It is particularly good with chicken, pork and any vegetable.

title: lithuanian kielbasa
directions: Through coarse grinder, pass fresh pork twice, then place in bowl.
Obtain pork bones from butcher and boil bones to create stock.
Add at least 2 cloves of garlic for each pound of ground meat.
Use more cloves to taste.
This is added to bowl of pork, crushed.
Add to bowl, 1 teaspoon of salt for each pound of pork. Add 1 small onion, diced fine, for each 2 pounds of pork.
Use stock to moisten the pork, creating mush like texture.
Use sheep casings and stuff manually or by machine rings of 1 to 2 pounds each.
Cook on medium-low in water in pot for 1 hour.
Serve with horseradish, plain or make a boiled dinner using cabbage, carrots and potato.

title: chicken bits
directions: *Either crush herb seasoned stuffing croutons or add 1/2 teaspoon sage and 1/2 teaspoon thyme to plain crumbs.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Beat up the eggs with the sugar; just beat to break up the eggs thoroughly and combine it with the sugar.
In a small pan, add the other ingredients (the butter, mustard and pepper).
Stir them together and then add the vinegar.
Place the pan over a slow flame and cook until the mixture thickens, like a soft custard. Stir constantly and slowly while cooking.
When the mixture thickens, remove from flame and chill.
When dressing is cold, mix it in thoroughly with the finely grated raw cabbage.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While cake is baking, melt caramel squares and rest of Eagle Brand milk in double boiler.
Pour over the partly baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over this.
Pour remaining cake batter over chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nana's pound cake("the best")
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Sift flour 3 times. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Add vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, a little at a time. Bake at 300° in tube or Bundt pan for about 2 hours.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Put melted butter in 11 x 17-inch baking dish, making sure to cover the bottom of the pan.
Pour croutons over butter; sprinkle cheese over croutons and set aside.
Combine milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour egg mixture over cheese; sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until set.

title: shrimp dip #1
directions: Blend well and serve with chips or crackers.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Cut corn kernels from cobs.
Measure 2 2/3 cups without packing down.
In a small skillet saute butter, onion and bell pepper until wilted.
In a medium bowl sift together cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper, milk and eggs.
Mix well, then add the corn and onion mixture.
Pour in a pan and bake in a 300° oven about 1 hour or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before cutting and serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza dough(serves 100)
directions: Put shortening and water in pan and cook until shortening melts.
Add some cold water (1/3 to 1/2 gallon).
Add flour mixture.
Add dissolved yeast.
Knead well.
The more you knead the better it is.
Divide.
Roll out and place filling on and bake in hot oven.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and jalapeno pepper (if desired) in oleo.
Cook rice and cream-style corn.
Add rice and corn to onion and pepper; mix good.
Pour in casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and starting to brown.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken in big heavy pan and cover with water.
Cook until meat falls off easily.
Cool and pull meat off bones.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Alternating dry ingredients with milk, add to wet mixture (don't add milk directly to dry ingredients).
Cook for 80 minutes at 325°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring butter, Karo syrup, sugar and salt to a boil.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Boil about 5 minutes, no longer.
Pour over 4 poppers of popcorn that have been kept warm. Stir well.

title: pistachio coconut surprise
directions: Combine ingredients in a Jell-O mold.
Chill or freeze.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour and baking powder together.
Add salt if you wish. Mix the oil and milk together and pour into flour.
Stir until mixed. Mold into 2 balls and cover the bowls with a towel. Allow to set while you prepare filling.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cornstarch dissolved in cool water to Jell-O mixture.
Cook until clear. Cool.
Peel and section grapefruit and cut into small pieces. Line pie shell with cream cheese.
Add Jell-O filling and top with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin impossible cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan (9 or 10-inch).
Beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute in blender or 2 minutes with hand mixer).
Pour into pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: banana-fruit muffins(without sugar)
directions: Beat together banana and eggs until creamy.
Add milk, vanilla and oil; beat well.
Measure in flour(s), baking soda and baking powder.
Mix; fold in fruit.
Spoon batter into oiled muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Makes 12.

title: margaret's brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla; mix with a spoon.
Add eggs.
Mix in well with spoon.
Combine flour and cocoa; add to mixture and stir only until mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Do not let them overbake or they won't be chewy.

title: sweet pickle spears
directions: Wash cucumbers, trim ends.
Cut lengthwise.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain cucumbers.
Heat ingredients to boiling.
Pack cucumbers in hot, sterile jars.
Pour hot liquid into jars until cucumbers are covered.
Process in boiling water 20 minutes.

title: red or green chile jelly
directions: Clean red chile pods; remove seeds.
Grind peppers, hot and sweet, in blender.
Add vinegar and sugar and boil until transparent.
Remove from stove and cool for 5 minutes.
Add Certo or Sure-Jel and stir thoroughly.
Pour into glasses and seal.

title: cinnamon-glazed pecans
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat egg white in 1-quart bowl until stiff.
Fold water and pecans into egg white.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pecan mixture.
Mix well.
Spread on nonstick or foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Stir to separate pecans.
Cool.

title: pennsylvania dutch oatmeal pie
directions: Combine sugars and salt.
Stir in beaten eggs and milk, mixing well.
Add oatmeal, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl and garnish with strawberries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	in microwave with no water.
Add margarine and
melt.	Add other ingredients and mix.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen. Need extra time to bake if frozen.

title: apricot-grapefruit salad
directions: Bring 1 cup nectar to boil; add Jell-O and dissolve.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup of the remaining nectar, then add to Jell-O mix.
Cool until thickened.
Pour into square glass dish.
Add pineapple and juice.
Remove membranes from sectioned citrus fruit and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Chill until firm, stirring occasionally.
Using the fresh citrus fruit gives this salad a delicious flavor.

title: pecan delights
directions: Mix caramels and milk over low heat until melted.
Stir in pecans and drop onto buttered wax paper.
Heat chocolate and wax on low heat until melted.
Dip caramel mix in chocolate and place on wax paper until cooled.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Parboil cauliflower for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Separate into small pieces.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar (will be crumbly).
Place about 2/3 of mixture in pie crust.
Mix pudding as directed on box, except use only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over peanut butter.
Let set until firm.
Add Cool Whip and top with the rest of peanut butter and confectioners sugar.

title: breasts of chicken with mushrooms
directions: Cut up the breasts into thin slices.
Immerse them in well-beaten eggs.
Let stand for 1 hour at least.
Roll them gently in bread crumbs.
Heat butter in casserole, but do not brown.
Fry the chicken slices in the butter.
When they are golden brown on one side, turn them over.
Cover them with the mushrooms.
Place the cheese strips on top.
Put casserole in 350° oven and cook 30 minutes, basting occasionally with the stock. Before taking to the table, squeeze as much lemon juice over as you think fitting.

title: mint gelatin
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water.
Add marshmallows until melted. Add pineapple, celery and chopped nuts.
In a separate bowl combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Stir into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until set.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots. Mix all ingredients well. Add a little lemon juice if you like. Makes 5 servings, 1/2 c. each.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook cubed squash and onion 5 minutes, until tender.
Drain. Mix soup, sour cream, salt and pepper with squash.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put half of stuffing in a baking dish. Put squash mixture on top, then top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine sugar, oil, and egg; beat until fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to pumpkin mixture, beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Spoon into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: hungarian sweet bread(kolach)
directions: Crumble yeast into water; stir until dissolved, then put aside.
Mix together the flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg, sour cream and yeast; mix thoroughly.
When smooth, work soft butter into mixture.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Put on a floured board and knead, then divide in 3.
Braid dough and put in a greased loaf pan.
Let rise, then bake in a 375°oven for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: turtle brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Heat over low heat until melted.
In mixing bowl using electric mixer, beat cake mix, butter and remaining milk until well mixed (1 minute).
Add nuts.
Press half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring, until smooth.
Combine remaining
milk mix and margarine; mix well. Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate pieces over crust; top with caramel mixture and spread to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoons of remaining cake mixture; press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts; press lightly into top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a heavy skillet until brown; drain off drippings.
Stir in garlic powder, cumin, salt and chili powder.
Set aside.
Combine soup and milk in a small saucepan. Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat and add sour cream; stir until well blended.
Set aside. Fry tortillas, one at a time, in 2 tablespoons hot oil (375°) for 3 to 5 seconds on each side or just until tortillas are softened. Drain on paper towels.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls beef mixture in center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese and roll up.
Place tortillas, seam side down, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sour cream mixture over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and garnish with ripe olives.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 5 minutes.

title: mexican cheese rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray nonfat cooking spray in a large casserole dish.
Saute onion in the Butter Buds for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in rice, yogurt, cottage cheese, bay leaf and pepper.
Mix well.
Layer half of the rice in a dish, then a layer of green chiles and cheeses.
Repeat, ending with Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Microwave butter in 2 qt. dish 20 seconds.
Stir in onion and brown sugar, cover with waxed paper and microwave on med. (5 minutes).
Stir in broth and water, cover with paper, microwave med. 10 minutes.
Place bread slices on plate, divide cheese among slices, microwave separate plate 20 seconds.
To serve, divide soup into 4 small bowls, place one cheese topped bread slice in each bowl, top with parsley and serve immediately.

title: potato icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar, salt and eggs together in a large bowl.
Add mashed potatoes and blend well. Add cooled down milk.
Next, add yeast mixture. Add flour, two cups at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Put in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Let set overnight.

title: pannekoken, dutch pancakesnetherlands
directions: Mix the flour with the salt. Make a hole in the middle and break the eggs into it. Add half of the milk and stir from the center out until the batter is smooth. Gradually beat in the rest of the milk. Cook pancakes on a hot griddle using the melted butter. Make them the size of pizzas! Serve with fruit and maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: skillet sweet-sour chops and cabbage
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Heat in a large skillet at 325°. Add chops and brown.
Combine and add remaining ingredients except cabbage.
Cover and reduce heat to 210°.
Cook for 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove chops.
Toss cabbage in sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and add celery, onion and sage to taste. Mix in chicken meat and soups.
Put in crock-pot and cook on low 4 hours or on high for 2 hours.
Cover while cooking.
You can use a regular chicken whole.
You can have broth, if needed.
You can add a little Ro-Tel for taste.

title: chili(crock-pot)
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 4 hours in crock-pot, on high for 30 minutes, then turn on low.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring sugar, milk and margarine to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Bring to soft ball stage; remove from heat and add peanut butter to taste (about 2 or 3 tablespoons).

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to box.
Layer in baking dish as follows:
wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat process.
Separate eggs, beat the whites until stiff, then beat in 1/4 cup of sugar. Put this over pudding as topping.
Put in oven at 400° until brown.

title: lillian mckee's wheat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in baking dish.
Spread on topping before baking.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, margarine and 2 eggs together and place in oblong cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over Cool Whip and mix well.
Add drained pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze out liquid.
In blender or processor, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill 24 hours.
Serve with raw veggies and crackers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs together in a large baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked roughy with caribbean sauce
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Spray a shallow baking pan with non-stick spray.
Lay fish fillets in bottom of baking dish. Season fish lightly with salt and pepper.
Bake fish in upper 1/3 of oven for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine sour cream, lime juice, cilantro, jalapeno and salt in a food processor or blender to make sauce.
Process 1 minute or until cilantro and jalapeno are finely chopped.
Slice carambola and lay over fillets.
Serve with sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons margarine; set aside.
Mix flour and water together.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add eggs and broccoli; stir well.
Add onions and pour in well-greased baking dish.
Add remaining margarine to cracker crumbs and sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: mexican cornbread with beef
directions: Brown hamburger and set aside.
Mix next 7 ingredients to make batter.
In a greased pan, pour 1/2 of batter; then layer hamburger, onion, chilies and grated cheese.
Pour remainder of batter on top.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
I usually use a 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in milk and cream cheese until well blended.
Add rest.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and egg pockets
directions: In large frying pan, cook beef over high heat, stirring, until pinkness is gone.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Mix together milk and onion.
Combine with eggs.
Place pan over medium heat.
Stir egg mixture into beef, stirring to scramble.
When eggs begin to set, stir in cheese.
Continue cooking until cheese melts and eggs are set.
Cut pockets in halves.
Place about 1/3 cup of hot mixture into each pocket.
Add tomato slices and alfalfa sprouts.
Serve 2 filled halves per person.

title: the greatest seafood chowder ever
directions: Saute the onions, carrots and celery in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add oregano, basil, thyme, salt and pepper with the potatoes and cook for about 10 minutes; add 1/2 cup of chicken broth if vegetables are sticking to the pan.
Add can of crushed tomatoes, sugar, chicken broth and just clam juice and cook/simmer for about 1-2 hours.
About 10 minutes before you are ready to serve add the clams and scallops.
I sometimes add small shrimp or langostino (tiny lobster tails) also.
After adding seafood, do not cook longer than 10 minutes or the clams, scallops and other seafood will be rubbery and tough.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together soda, flour and sugar.
In saucepan, bring to rapid boil 1 stick oleo, 1/4 cup cocoa, shortening and water. Pour over flour and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Wash apples; core and cut into chunks.
Slice bananas.
Drain pineapple; add lemon juice and toss together with remaining ingredients.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coffee rolls
directions: Place rolls in a greased Bundt cake pan.
Mix together other ingredients and shake over rolls.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over this.
It is suggested to prepare this the night before and let set in oven overnight; then bake the next morning for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before turning out onto a plate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Split pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper inside and out.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff loosely into the chops.
Fasten with wooden picks.
Brown in hot grease on both sides, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake, covered, in baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender.

title: corn custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1-quart casserole.

title: fat-free white sauce
directions: Bring milk and salt to boil.
Add the cream of rice and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Blend until smooth.

title: chicken dressing
directions: And no garden is complete with turnips:

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Add cold water and chill for 1 hour.
Add sour cream and pecans.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: cottage cheese (schmierkase) pie
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, salt and flour; mix well.
Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell; sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes longer or until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer 1: Place torn lettuce in bottom of dish.

title: mixed vegetable creole
directions: Cut open squash and scoop out seeds.
Fill each shell with diced onions, green peppers, mushrooms and celery.
You may also add some chopped zucchini squash.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Stir in 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Drizzle over chopped vegetables inside squash and around cut edge.
Put squash in 8 x 8-inch pan with 1/4 cup water in bottom.
Salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon crushed basil.
Place in oven preheated at 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Serve over a bed of wild rice.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, prepare the rice as directed; set aside.

title: pink rice
directions: Soak rice in water in a heavy saucepan for 30 minutes.
Drain and discard water.
Saute rice in butter in the same pan.
Add stock, salt, paprika and pepper.
Stir to blend spices.
Cover; bring to a boil and cook 12 to 15 minutes or until rice is almost tender.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip low-fat cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, eggs and 3/4 of the chocolate chips.
Place in pie crust pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips on top. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn dogs
directions: Place a small stick in each hot dog.
Mix other ingredients together.
Dip hot dogs into mixture and fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin-chocolate chip muffins
directions: In large bowl mix eggs, sugar, brown sugar, pumpkin and oil.
In separate bowl combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon; blend with egg mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15-20 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Cream cottage cheese in blender or food processor.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Add dry orange jello, mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple; mix together, then chill.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream the Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Crush 1/2 cup of berries and add to batter.
Fold in remaining berries and spoon into muffin pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes and turn onto rack.

title: teresa's chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger and peppers; drain off fat.
Add everything together; blend and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Dip nacho chips and enjoy.
Can be reheated.

title: chicken tagine from morocco(tagine means "stew")
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute. Add stock to cover.
Add carrots, salt, pepper and spices (except bay leaves).
Cover and simmer until done.
May be made to this point ahead of time.
Just before serving, reheat with prunes and olives.
Serve with rice or couscous with bay leaves tucked in to slightly flavor food.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Form into a ball, then roll in nuts.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: thai salad(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Cook pasta as directed, drain well and mix with oil combination.
Chill.
Blanch pea pods 2 to 3 minutes; drain and chill.
Place scallions, cilantro (or coriander), ginger root, garlic, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, sugar, salt and pepper in blender and blend well until liquified.
Pour over chilled pasta and gently mix.
Gently toss in whole (or slivered) pea pods. Save a few for garnish if you like.
Also, garnish with chopped nuts!
You may add 1/2 to 1 pound cooked shrimp, chicken or beef if you like.

title: grandma annie's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar, add in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream and vanilla.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until lightly brown 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. In larger bowl, beat egg yolks and brown sugar until mixture is light in color and thickened.
Blend in peanut butter and corn syrup. Gradually beat in milk and vanilla. Fold egg whites into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.

title: microwave tuna and rice casserole
directions: Blend cheese and soup in bowl.
Add tuna, rice, green onion, parsley and pepper.
Spoon in 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Microwave on High 3 to 6 minutes or until heated through.

title: chess squares
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over cake mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: knox blox
directions: In large bowl, mix unflavored and flavored gelatines.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 9 dozen blocks.

title: overnight berry patch coffee cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot batter with preserves.
Swirl preserves through batter to give marble effect.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture in 4 parts, beating just until smooth, after each addition.
Mix in oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: large chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken thighs until tender.
Remove from bones. Thicken the broth with the 1/4 cup flour or cornstarch mixed with water.

Add the margarine. Using the self-rising flour, shortening and water, make a stiff dough. Divide in half. Roll thin and place strips around sides of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Put chicken chunks in pan. Thinly sliced the eggs and place over the chicken. Salt to taste.
Pour the thickened broth over the chicken, enough to cover.
Roll the other half of dough and cover the chicken. Spread enough margarine over the crust to thinly cover.
Bake at 400° until crust is browned.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix.
Bake
at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes on greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: easy-mix cookies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients, then stir in the package of cake mix.
Add oatmeal or other desired "yummy."
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes at 375°, until top springs back to light touch.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Add eggs; gradually add flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: heavenly dish
directions: Mix all ingredients into Cool Whip; chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add other fruit, if desired.
Make 1 to 2 days ahead.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Spread with mayonnaise to cover all.
Sprinkle sugar over top and layer the cheese and bacon. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Toss thoroughly before serving.

title: raisin cheese slaw
directions: In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, lemon juice, sugar, salt, mustard and onion powder.
In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot, cheese and raisins.
Fold in dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: barbecue pheasant casserole
directions: Arrange pheasant on bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix onions, sauce and syrup; pour over meat.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: salmon stew
directions: Place diced potatoes and onions in large pot; cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat down; simmer an hour or so.
Add salmon; cook about 15 minutes. Add milk; heat until very hot.
Do not boil.
Serve with saltines.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, take skin off first, cool and debone.
Make Rotel dip with Velveeta cheese (melt together in Microwave). Crush chips on bottom of pan.
Cut up chicken, add to cooked rice, then add soup, then Rotel dip.
Pour over chips and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together, form into balls and bake until browned at 400°.

title: skillet beans-cabbage
directions: Remove pork from beans and mash into bacon fat.
Heat fat. Add cabbage and cover.
Cook over moderate heat about five minutes.
Stir in beans, cream or milk.
Add seasoning.
Cover and continue cooking five more minutes or until cabbage is very tender.
Makes 4 average servings.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Time of preparation: 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in pan; add a cup of peanut butter and 1 can milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: broiled fillet of white fish
directions: Sauce:
Melt butter. Blend in flour.
Beat in egg yolk, then lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Add soup and water; stir.
Add rice and simmer 5 minutes.
Arrange cabbage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered dish. Add carrot and cubed cheese on top.
Pour meat mixture over all this.
Do not stir!
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: caviar rounds
directions: Butter rounds or rye toast.
Press on these rounds slices of the egg white; fill the inside of the egg white with caviar. Sprinkle finely minced onion over caviar.
Surround egg white with grated yolk.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients except 7-Up and freeze.
To serve, fill tall glass half full of slush mixture and add 7-Up.

title: strawberries (candied)
directions: Mix and roll in balls, then shape like strawberries and roll in red sugar.

title: chinese eggrolls
directions: Steam cabbage, lettuce, onions, celery and pepper until soft, but not mushy.
Stir-fry in 1/4 cup of oil, the meat for 3 minutes. Add water chestnuts and cook 5 minutes.
Add cabbage mixture and stir.
Add bean sprouts and cook until soft.
Place small amount on eggroll skin, fold and seal with small amount of egg yolk.
Deep fry in 1/2 inch of oil.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form two logs.
Roll in foil and chill. Roll in dried parsley flakes and ground pecans.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Pour can of pineapple into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish then pour can of blueberries on top of pineapple.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans, then pour dry cake mix over the top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lamb chop and potato scallop
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, water and dill weed in a small bowl. Blend well.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add the sauce.
Dissolve. Add the pineapple; mix.
Pour 1 layer in bowl; refrigerate until set.
Add layer of sour cream.
Add layer of Jell-O.
Refrigerate. Continue until all Jell-O is used.

title: cheese balls
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour gradually, stirring mixture constantly.
Add salt, paprika and green pepper.
Beat cheese into well beaten egg.
Add cheese and egg mixture to sauce.
Cook over hot water until cheese is melted.
Stir constantly.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Mold into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in bread crumbs; dip in slightly beaten egg which should be diluted with 2 tablespoons water.
Roll again in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Do not overcook. Drain on paper towels.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone, set aside.
Cook egg noodles in the chicken broth that you cooked the chicken in, you may have to add extra water to the broth.
Meanwhile, saute bell pepper in a little butter until tender.
Save the butter sauce.
When the egg noodles are tender drain all but about 1/4 of the broth in the pot as this will help it be creamy.
In the large pot that you boiled chicken and egg noodles in combine all ingredients, mix well.
Hint:
Just pour butter and bell pepper directly from saute pan into the mixture, the butter makes it even better.
If you don't like cornflakes then leave ingredients in pot and slowly cook over medium heat while stirring, just until cheese is melted, serve & enjoy.
If you prefer cornflakes, heat oven to 425°, transfer mixture to a large baking dish, and crumble cornflakes over mixture.
Bake until cheese is melted and cornflakes are good and crunchy.
Great for Thanksgiving, or anytime.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough.
If not, scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with butter and seasonings.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add soup, water and seasoning. Cover; simmer 3 hours until tender.
Stir now and then.
Remove meat.
Gradually blend 1/4 cup water with flour.
Slowly stir into gravy.
Cook until thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Cook rice and set aside. Cook black-eyed peas with the meat of your choice. Set aside. Melt oleo. Add garlic, onion, celery and bell pepper.

Add water and sugar. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for about 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add this to cooked black-eyed peas and meat. Mix thoroughly, then mix with rice. Add green onions and parsley. Leave on hot burner.
Sprinkle each serving lightly with gumbo file.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Work in the butter.
Mix until texture is crumbly.
Spread fruit evenly in buttered shallow baking pan.
Spread crumb mixture on top of rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until rhubarb is soft and crumb mixture is golden brown.
Serve warm with or without cream.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 count muffin pan.
Mix cereal, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Stir in remaining ingredients until moistened.
Pour equally into muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 22 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight so that the spices can release full flavor.

title: squash relish
directions: Sprinkle squash and bell pepper with salt.
Let set overnight in ice water.
Rinse and drain well.
Add celery, onion, pimento, sugar, vinegar, mustard, turmeric and pickling spice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to boil; turn heat down and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: succotash
directions: Simmer celery and chopped onion until tender in the liquid drained from beans.
The liquid, by this time, should be almost evaporated.
Add corn, drained beans, pimiento, milk and butter. Simmer until thoroughly heated.
Salt to suit taste and serve at once.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts and set aside.
Take 1 cup flour and mix with fruit to keep it from sticking together. Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into fruit, adding whiskey last.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed meat roll
directions: Combine hamburger, egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and basil.
Flatten meat out in a square until meat is about 3/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle grated cheese and vegetables on meat.
Roll up into a loaf.
Make sure all areas are patched so cheese doesn't seep out during baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with scalloped potatoes and Italian-style green beans.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples.
Slice medium thin.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cook 10 minutes or until a fork can be inserted through them.

title: english pea recipe
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in 1/2 stick butter.
Mix this with rest of ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs browned in butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: crispy oriental asparagus
directions: Heat peanut oil on medium.
Add garlic, ginger and sugar. Boil but do not let it burn.
Add soy sauce and vinegar.
Cook 1 minute.
Add sesame oil.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add fruit juices and bananas.
Mix well.
Chill.
To serve, combine with lemon-lime soda; stir well. Yields 1 gallon.

title: strawberry-cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in a cup of hot water.
Put in frozen berries and mashed bananas.
When this begins to set, pour half in a dish and spread sour cream over it, then put in rest of jello mixture.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain well.
Mash potatoes; add all other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: laura bush cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; beat. Add dry ingredients until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: minnie's tea cakes
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs with a fork or whisk.
Stir in flour; start with 2 cups and add more if needed.
You want to have batter stiff enough to roll.
Add flavoring.
Put flour on your hands and pinch a small piece of the batter.
Make a ball out of the batter and press down on a greased cookie sheet.
Space the tea cakes about 2 inches apart as they will spread when they begin to cook.
Bake in a 400° oven for approximately 8 minutes.
Tea cakes are done when the edges look a little brown.
This recipe comes from Billy's family's maid, Minnie Pearl Cooper.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli (some stems) into bite-size pieces.
Mix together with all other ingredients.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and melted butter.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Top with 1/2 box corn flakes sauteed in 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown and flaky.
Cool.

title: country style steak-in-the-pot
directions: Cut steak into serving portions.
Coat with flour.
Brown on both sides in shortening in a skillet.
Place in a crock-pot. Sprinkle onion over steak.
Add soup and water to pan drippings in skillet; mix well.
Pour over steak.
Cook on low for 6 hours or until tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: clemson "tigerific" cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream butter/margarine, sugar, and vanilla. Add flour a little at a time until dough is smooth.
Add crushed potato chips last, folding in well.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet or shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until cookie bottoms are golden brown.

title: cream shrimp
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add chopped garlic.
Add shrimp; cook until pink.
Cook in small amount of water the chopped celery, pepper and onion until tender.
Drain water and add shrimp.
Add mushroom soup.
Cook on low until well heated.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch squares.
Brown in 1 tablespoon hot shortening.
Remove meat; add gravy mix and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil and add all but the noodles.
Pour over meat in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: reuben rods
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat cookie sheet with Pam.
Finely chop corned beef and sauerkraut.
Combine with cheese and mustard in small bowl.
Place one sheet of phyllo dough on waxed paper (keep remaining phyllo covered with damp towel).
Brush sheet lightly with oil.
Spoon 3 tablespoons beef mixture in
thin strips along short edge to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Roll up, folding up edges as rolling.
Place, seam side down.
Score crosswise to make 4 equal rods.
Brush with oil.
Repeat with remaining.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes or lightly brown. Cut each in 4 rods.
Serve warm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread crumbs and stir. Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand before serving. Great for brunch.

title: apple dumplings(german style)
directions: Boil the sugar, water, butter and cinnamon for 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Roll favorite pie crust into squares. Core but do not peel the apples.
Slice and place in center of crust.
Pour liquid over dumplings. Seal crust and twist.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes. Baste every 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain (omit salt).
Place in buttered dish and dot with margarine.
Mix together cheese, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour over broccoli and mix slightly. Sprinkle with stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: cherub puff cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Cover baking sheet with wax paper or foil.
To the 2 egg whites, which beat lighter at room temperature, add the salt, vanilla and either the vinegar or cream of tartar. Beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the sugar.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in the chocolate chips and the nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto covered cookie sheets, approximately half dollar size.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove with spatula to rack to cool. Store loosely covered.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 dozen.
Double recipe, if desired.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Put the sugar, water and corn syrup into a heavy saucepan. Stir it while it dissolves over the fire, then let it boil, without stirring, to the light crack stage (265°).
While it is cooking, beat the whites of eggs stiffly and when the syrup is ready, pour it over them, beating constantly.
Beat until creamy. Add nuts, cherries and extract.
Drop from teaspoon on buttered plates.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done, then mash with 1/2 cup or more of water.
Mix in all ingredients.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat cake for 4 minutes, until light.
Add nuts and maraschino cherries.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in Nestle bits and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine both packages of gelatin and fix according to directions on package.
Let cool.
Mix cranberries, orange, sugar and nuts.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: green bean salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and set aside.
Let cool; then add salad oil and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid over vegetables and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Drain before serving.

title: macaroons i
directions: Whisk egg whites stiffly.
Stir in almonds, sugar, ground rice and flavorings.
Grease baking sheet or flat pan.
Cover with greased brown paper.
Place mixture in heaps (small) or pipe small rounds, leaving room to spread.
Place an almond on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
It is important to bake macaroons slowly to allow to color evenly and get a good texture.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Boil corn syrup, sugar and cream until it forms a solid ball in a cup of cold water.
Beat hard by hand until it wants to set. Add cherries and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered cake pan and chill.
Cut into desired pieces and store in a tight container.

title: date crisps
directions: Bring the margarine and sugar to a boil.
Add the egg and dates.
Cook 10 minutes on very low heat. Cool. Add the Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Make into small balls or a log.
Roll in the coconut.

title: pot roast perfect
directions: Place sheet of aluminum foil, long enough to fold over roast and seal edges, into 9 inch x 13 inch casserole dish.
Place beef on foil.
Combine all other ingredients.
Stir and pour over meat spreading to cover.
Fold foil over roast and crimp edges to seal securely.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours until tender.
Open foil and spoon juices over roast.
Slice and serve with cooking juices. May use a large crock pot.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Peel oranges, apples and bananas and dice.
Add nuts, sugar and lemon juice and mix well.
This salad is best served as a dessert.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and green peppers in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Whip all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes 3 cups.

title: hamburger roast
directions: Add all ingredients together in a pot. Cook until the meat and veggies are done.

title: broiled lamb patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Arrange on broiler rack leaving 2-inches between the surface of the patties and the heat.
Broil on one side until brown, about 10 minutes.
Turn and brown the other side.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix together until smooth.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk. Add cheese and 1/2 crumbs.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Add rest of crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Combine spinach and cottage cheese, salt, Parmesan cheese and eggs; blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased shallow casserole (7 x 11-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Excellent for a brunch.

title: maple-glazed pork tenderloins
directions: Sprinkle tenderloins with salt and pepper.
Place pork in bowl; cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cocoa, oil, flour, baking powder and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, greased and floured.
Spread on marshmallow cream while cake is warm.
Top with icing.

title: quick and easy hot rolls
directions: Put yeast in water, allow to dissolve.
Add oil.
Mix other ingredients together.
Combine all.
Knead, roll and cut out. Allow to rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook at 450° approximately 5 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes until batter is well blended and glossy.
Cover bottom of well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan with 1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar and 2 tablespoons melted butter.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Beat well.
Add lemon juice.
Blend well.
Pour into well chilled graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 30 minutes before spooning the cherry pie filling on top.
Spread topping evenly over the filling.
Place in freezer at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and 1/2 cup margarine (melted) together.
Place in greased casserole dish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes lots of cookies.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and clear jel.
Add water to berries.
Spread cream cheese over bottom and sides of pie crust.
Line inside of shell with whole strawberries.
Add sugar mixture to mashed berries and pour over crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: molasses peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix oil, peanut butter, eggs, molasses and brown and white sugars.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well and add oatmeal.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Break off as far down as asparagus stalks snap easily.
Place stalks in single layers in ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Sprinkle with seasoned salt, salt and water.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake until tender 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caponata
directions: Saute eggplant, onion and pepper in oil until eggplant is tender and browned slightly. Add the remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Heat mixture thoroughly. Serve at room temperature with crackers and cheese. This dish is better made ahead to allow the flavors to blend.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix the sugars, shortening and salt.
Add the eggs and mix. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Dip the bottom of a glass first in water and then in sugar; flatten cookies with it.
Bake cookies at 350° until very lightly browned.
Don't overcook or they will be crunchy, not chewy.

title: cinnamon peaches
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Combine ingredients and pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sour cream raisin pie(a covered wagon days pie)
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and cloves and blend in.
Fold in sour cream and raisins. Pour into pastry lined pie pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter baking dish; place rice in bottom of dish.
Add chicken.
Mix other ingredients together in bowl; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rosemary leg of lamb
directions: In a bowl, combine the garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper; rub over meat. Place on a rack in a large roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours or until the meat reaches desired doneness (for rare, a meat thermometer should read 140°, medium 160° and well-done 170°). Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternating to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add flavorings and mace.
Spoon batter in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Top with sifted powdered sugar.

title: brownies in a cone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cones in muffin tins.

Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Spoon batter into cones 3/4 full. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until tops are cracked and have risen above the rims of the cones. Remove the cones from oven and cool to room temperature.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Use about 5 ounces of oil. Mix all ingredients (crock-pot best) and bring to a good bubbling boil for 15 minutes.
Simmer for at least 3 hours or more. Brown 2 pounds of hamburger meat and drain.
Add to simmering sauce and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: *See Broccoli With Pork recipe, follows.
Combine ingredients.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add milk and melted shortening.
Stir until smooth.
Spread in greased baking pan 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Spread cherries over batter then last mix 1/2 cup sugar, butter and cherry juice.
Bring to boil and pour over cherries.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix up all ingredients until mixed thoroughly.
Take dough and roll out.
Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown on bottom.

title: creamy wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Prepare the wild rice.
Meanwhile, combine the soup with the dairy sour cream, stirring to blend well.
Melt the butter in a skillet and saute the celery, onion and mushrooms just until vegetables are slightly limp.
Stir in salt, pepper, cream-soup mixture, wild rice and turkey.
Spoon into a shallow 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°, then uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-caramel apples
directions: Place caramels and water in large measuring cup.
Microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir once halfway through.
Wash and dry apples. Place wooden skewer in stem end of each. Dip into warm caramel to coat. Wipe off excess.
Place on greased waxed paper and chill until set.

title: gullivar's corn
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter and flour, then add to corn.
Mix well, then pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan, cayenne, parsley, etc.; and bake for a few minutes (just until the top browns around edges).

title: green tomato relish
directions: Pour salt over green
tomatoes,
onions and peppers and let stand 1 or 2 hours, then
drain.
Bring to boil for 1 or 2 minutes the cinnamon, allspice,
celery
salt, sugar and vinegar.
Add chopped vegetables;
boil
again
for
minutes. Pour in jars and seal.

title: whiskey cookies
directions: Cut up all the fruit into small pieces and chop the pecans. Dust the whole pile with the 1/2 cup of flour.
Cream the Crisco and sugar, adding the eggs, bourbon, flour and spices.
Mix well and pour over the dusted
fruit and nuts.
Stir until well mixed. Drop on a greased cookie sheet with a teaspoon and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie 2
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, blend together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add melted butter and beat until creamy.
In a different bowl, beat eggs lightly and beat together with the buttermilk, lemon rind and juice.
Add to flour mixture and blend well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: cold lemon souffle(light and tart; rich, but not heavy)
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Gradually adding lemon juice until mixture becomes thick.
In saucepan over low heat, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool and add to lemon mixture.
Partially whip 1 pint cream until thickened but not stiff and fold into mixture. Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff peaks form and fold into mixture.
Line sides and bottom of 2-quart glass bowl with ladyfingers and fill with lemon mixture. Chill and serve topped with whipped cream.
Or pour mixture into parfait glasses, chill and garnish with twist of lemon.
Serves 12.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over salad.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add soda to flour. Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 3 layers at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Makes a great breakfast food or party snack.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Soak in salted cold water to wash and get rid of any aphides.
Parboil in salted water about 10 minutes.
Drain water and run under cold water to stop cooking. Into small bowl, break and slightly beat egg, milk and pinch of salt.
Into another bowl put 1 cup crumbs.
Add more crumbs as needed.
Dip each floweret into egg mixture.
Coat well, then into crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until brown, turning to brown all sides.

title: savory chicken stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package.
Do not let stand as directed.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, spoon stuffing down center of dish, leaving space on both sides of stuffing.
Arrange 3 pieces of chicken on each side of stuffing.

title: green cabbage salad
directions: Blend sugar, oil, vinegar and salt to make dressing.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: smothered mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine.
Combine rest of ingredients (except Parmesan) with mushroom mixture.
After chicken has baked for 30 minutes, take out of oven and pour mushroom mixture over it.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake another 20 to 30 minutes.
If serving over rice, double the sauce ingredients for extra.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip or refried beans and seasoning on a flat platter.
Top with chopped onions.
Spread on sour cream and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle on olives and peppers.
Serve with corn chips.

title: onion pie
directions: In a 2-quart buttered casserole or an 8-inch square baking dish, place crushed crackers in bottom.
Sprinkle grated Swiss cheese over top; set aside.

title: fruit (corn) fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat oil in pan, medium heat.
When hot, spoon in mixture 1 teaspoon at a time making small balls.
Turn once when browned, drain on paper towels and serve while still hot with syrup.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Melt cheese. Add milk to thin cheese. Add chili and Tabasco sauce if desired. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all together with electric beater.
Pour into three 9-inch pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: make ahead freezer sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put on sandwich buns.
Wrap individually in aluminum foil and wrap tight.
When ready to eat, take out 1 or more sandwiches.
Heat in a 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 sandwiches.
May be wrapped in plastic wrap and heated in microwave with small opening in wrap.

title: spicy coleslaw(this tasty dish uses less sugar, salt and fat)
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, cucumber, tomato, green pepper and green onions; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; fold in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and margarine together. Press into a 9 x 13 inch pan saving 2-3 tablespoons of the crumbs. Put in the refrigerator for 45 minutes.

title: georgia's salmon cakes
directions: Heat skillet and cooking oil until hot. Fry salmon cakes on one side, then turn and fry until golden brown.

title: potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in large pot. Add flour and salt; stir. Add the milk slowly until it thickens. Add potatoes and bring to a boil. Pour in large dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham rolls
directions: Pour mixture over rolls.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: big batch cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl, beat with electric mixer until blended. Add sugar, mix well.

Add flour to sugar mixture beating until well blended. Stir in cereal to remaining ingredients (by hand). Drop by level tablespoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool. Yields 6 - 7 dozen.

title: fried squirrel arkansas
directions: Put chicken stock, white wine, minced onion, rosemary, parsley, salt, pepper and squirrel pieces in large saucepan or Dutch oven. Remove squirrel pieces and set aside while stock continues to cook at a simmer.
Beat eggs.
Pour into shallow pan.
Place corn meal in similar pan.
Roll squirrel pieces in egg, then meal.
Set aside at least 10 minutes, then roll again.
Melt butter in large skillet and cook garlic.
Brown squirrel pieces in same butter until tender.
Remove stock from heat and strain.
Add 2/3 cup to skillet and stir and scrape all brown bits over low heat until gravy thickens.
Serve with rice, potatoes or grits.
