title: orange salad
directions: Mix above ingredients and refrigerate.

title: lill's marinated carrots
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, soup and Worcestershire sauce together in a saucepan.
Heat, stirring thoroughly.
Add onion and pepper.
Pour mixture over carrots and mix.
Store in refrigerator as long as desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place 1 chicken in buttered baking dish with rice in bottom of the dish.
Mix soups with milk and salt.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix(for diabetics)
directions: Mix well and store in container with tight fitting lid.
To use, put 1/3 cup mixture into cup.
Fill with hot water.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of cupcake papers.
Fill with mixture 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and no longer.
Cool.
Top with any type of pie filling (cherry, blueberry, etc.).
Makes 12 to 16 cupcakes.

title: penuche
directions: Boil syrup and milk together for 15 minutes or until forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add nuts, salt and vanilla, beating until creamy.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper. When cool, cut in squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, soup and margarine; mix well. Add salt, onion and cheese; mix well.
Place mixture in shallow, 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in oven, preheated to 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter oat bars
directions: Spread oats on a cookie sheet and toast 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven. Stir oats occasionally.

title: frozen pineapple cherry salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice well.
Mix other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream last.
Freeze.
Will keep a month.
Cut in squares to serve.
Pour mixture in Pyrex and cover to freeze.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring peanut butter and Karo syrup to a boil. Gradually add sugar.
Pour over cornflakes. Mix and pat into a large Pyrex bowl. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: super hot dish with rice
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
The last half hour of baking, cover with crushed potato chips.
This casserole can be made in advance and placed in the freezer unbaked.

title: cheesy corn
directions: Drain corn.
Melt butter and cheese together.
Mix all together and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli polonaise
directions: Saute 1 minced garlic clove, onion, parsley or cilantro in butter.
When butter bubbles, stir in breadcrumbs.
Remove from heat and season with salt and lemon juice.
Blanch 4 portions of broccoli tops in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and let sit for 2 minutes.
Arrange hot broccoli on plate and spoon small amount of warm bread sauce over each portion.

title: date balls
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, sugar, dates and Pet milk for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla. Let cool; roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Roll hard-boiled eggs in flour.
Wrap in hot sausage.
Roll in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs with sage added.
Fry in deep hot oil for 10 to 12 minutes until very brown.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set 24 hours in tight container in refrigerator.
Keeps 3 weeks.

title: chile maize(corn)
directions: Put strained meat grease (bacon, etc.) in heavy skillet and warm. Add the corn and spices. Simmer to thicken corn by about 1/3.
Stir occasionally to prevent forming a crust on the bottom of the pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Blend together the mayonnaise and soup.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top casserole with dried onion rings.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all ingredients together and cook 35 to 40 minutes. Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix cooked rice, broccoli, soup, mushrooms, cheese, onion, celery and water chestnuts together.
Put mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add 1/3 of sugar and beat well.
Add egg, vanilla, salt and milk; beat until smooth.
Add remaining sugar until smooth.
Will frost a 2-layer cake.

title: halloween punch
directions: Mix orange and grape Kool-Aid according to package directions to make black punch.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese and bread crumbs) and pour into a large buttered casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry jello dessert
directions: Prepare jello as directed; let set until almost done.
Add the cranberries to jello mixture; mix well.
Top with miniature marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Return to refrigerator until serving time.

title: cheddar cheese corn meal muffins
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Beat egg, milk and butter. Add the dry ingredients.
Add cheese.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes in buttered muffin tins.
You may freeze and reheat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream vanilla, sugar, butter and water (a little pinch of salt).
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well and shape into little balls the size of walnuts.
Use remainder of sugar and sift into a bag, drop cookies in and shake carefully.
When cookies get brown on the bottom, they are done.
They never get brown on top.
Put in a cool oven and bake at 300° or slightly hotter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Some ovens may be 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Melt jelly and chili sauce together over low heat.
Add the hot dogs and heat until warm.
May be done in crock-pot.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, pour into casserole dish and bake one hour at 350°.

title: chicken rice wraps
directions: Saute chicken in a little vegetable oil. You can season the chicken with salt and pepper if you desire. Cook thoroughly and cube. Slice and saute mushrooms and bell pepper in butter. In a medium sized oven safe dish, combine all ingredients, excluding tortillas, in the dish and mix. Bake in 425° oven covered for 25 minutes or until broth is absorbed and rice is fully cooked. Heat up tortillas 5 at a time in microwave. Simply dampen two paper towels, place tortillas between them and cook for 45 seconds on high. Place the rice mixture inside tortillas wrap and enjoy. Also great served with picante sauce spread on them.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Peel and cut carrots into bite size pieces.
Cut celery into bite size pieces.
Combine celery, carrots and onions and boil until tender.
Drain.
Pour into bowl and mix thoroughly with cream of mushroom soup.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: pineapple marshmallow sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange sweet potatoes and pineapple in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
In medium saucepan, combine reserved juice, 10 marshmallows, brown sugar and margarine.
Cook and stir until marshmallows melt; pour over potatoes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with remaining marshmallows. Return to oven 5 minutes or until marshmallows are soft and lightly browned.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Flour bottom of 13 X 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 for 35-40 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Very moist cake.
Leave plain or sprinkle with confection sugar.

title: hot brown
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan melt butter.
Add flour and whisk in milk until thickened.	Add cheese, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until melted.
Toast bread and line the bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish; place turkey on top of turkey. Pour cheese sauce on top of cheese sauce; bake in oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: roberto's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an ungreased pie pan for 25 minutes at 325°.
When cool, add sliced bananas and Cool Whip. Delicious and different.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Chop nuts.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff. Add sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and crackers. Pour in greased and floured pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream with added sugar and vanilla.

title: toastees
directions: Melt together the butter and margarine.
Cut bread in triangular pieces. Dip into butter mixture.
Dip or sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put on baking sheet.
Broil until toasty brown. Enjoy!

title: laura's favorite some-mores
directions: Toast 2 marshmallows very slowly so it will be hot and gooey all the way to center.
Have ready a cracker, topped with chocolate.
Use a spoon to push marshmallows off the stick.
Squish lid down.
Then enjoy!

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add uncooked rice, peas, tomatoes, green pepper (can use 1/2 cup), salt and pepper.
Heat. Pour into Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Be sure there is enough liquid for rice to cook.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, water, salt, cinnamon and allspice together in heavy saucepan.
Boil over medium heat until 238°, or until candy thermometer reaches soft boil stage.
Add nuts and stir until sugared.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cool and separate into serving pieces.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend together well.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 large servings.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Peel potatoes and put them into cold water.
Put 1 potato in a deep spoon.
Slice it down to the spoon about 1/8-inch apart.
Return potato to water.
Repeat with rest of potatoes.
Drain potatoes and pat dry.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Baste them with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle fine bread crumbs over each potato and baste with butter.
Continue cooking until tender.
Parmesan cheese may be added 5 minutes before removing.
Serves 4.

title: chewy fudge brownies
directions: Blend cocoa and 1/3 cup oil; add boiling water.
Stir until it thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs
and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts (optional).
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in 4x sugar or coconut.
Store in airtight container.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: In a 4-quart glass bowl, melt oleo in microwave about 45 seconds.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High until mixture boils (1 to 3 minutes).
Stir once.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, without stirring.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Stir in popcorn.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Stir again and microwave 1 minute more.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: pork casserole(yield:  24 servings)
directions: Mix all together and bake in a casserole at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in top part of double boiler. Gradually stir in milk and cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg and add a small amount of milk mixture.
Return to boiler and cook for 2 minutes over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and extract; cool.
Slice 2 bananas into baked shell.
Pour cooked mixture over bananas at once.
Chill for at least 1 hour. Put coconut in shallow pan and toast in oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: caramels
directions: Boil until
heavy syrup.
Add, but do not stop boiling, oleo and
canned
milk.	Boil
until
hard ball stage; pour on buttered pan.
Cut and wrap.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and chopped onions in boiling salted water 3 minutes.
Drain and combine with next 3 ingredients.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and spread 1/2 in 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Add vegetable mix and sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes as directed for boiled potatoes.
Drain.
Cube potatoes and combine with celery, green pepper, vinegar, seasoning and chopped eggs.
Toss lightly to mix.
Add bacon fat.
Spoon into an 8-inch glass dish.
Cook with microwave for 9 minutes. Top with cheese.
Cook 4 minutes longer.
Recipe yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine.
Spread over cake batter and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Empty can of pineapple into the measuring cup and finish filling with cold water to make up the other 2 cups added to jello.
Mix in cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into bowl or mold and place in refrigerator until set.
Serve with Ritz crackers or Waverly Wafers.

title: grandma rose's easiest cookie you'll ever make
directions: Mix by hand into a large ball.
Make small balls (about the size of a large marshmallow) and use fork to press down the cookie. Cookies should be about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Cookie will be slightly brown on the bottom.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tuna romanoff
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and next 3 ingredients; saute for 6 minutes or until tender.
Combine milk and next 6 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Add mushroom mixture, noodles and next 3 ingredients.
Stir gently.
Spoon noodle mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: homemade cupcakes
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the vanilla and eggs.
Add the flour mixture and alternate with milk.
Spoon batter into cupcake forms.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 14 to 16 large cupcakes.

title: jalapeno cornbread casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except for ground beef and cheese; brown ground beef and grate cheese.
Grease pan, pour 1/2 batter in, then add the meat and cheese.
Pour in remaining batter.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Pour butter mixture over fruit in casserole.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 325°.

title: baked beans
directions: Put in casserole dish and bake in
a 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown and thickened.

title: crunch-crust brownies
directions: Combine first four ingredients
in
a
small
bowl; mix well. Press mixture into a
greased
9-inch
square pan.
Set aside. Combine brownie mix, hot water, oil and egg in a large mixing bowl.
Mix with a
wooden
spoon
until blended.
Spoon over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: katie fleming's molasses cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add molasses and butter.
Mix well and then add the balance of ingredients until smooth.
Bake in a 300° to 350° oven for 30 minutes or until firm in middle.
Fills one square pan.

title: swirl cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust. Dot top of cheesecake with preserves.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: tacoma chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, boil next 4 items. Combine buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla and add to all other items. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chinese green beans
directions: Place beans in a large pot and steam 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Cool under running water; drain.
Mix soy sauce, water, cornstarch, sugar, sesame oil and red pepper in bowl until blended.
Heat oil in pot or wok.
Add beans and stir-fry 3 minutes or until beans are very hot and begin to char in spots. Add garlic and ginger root.
Continue stir-frying several minutes more.
Pour in soy sauce mixture.
Toss beans constantly until evenly coated and glazed.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Makes 20 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Put cornflake crumbs on top.

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Blend butter, corn syrup and vanilla.
Mix sugar and dry milk gradually.
Add to syrup mixture.
Knead until thoroughly blended. Shape into 3/4-inch rolls, 6 inches long.
Score into bite size pieces with a sharp knife.
Wrap in waxed paper and twist.
Makes 36.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and vanilla.
Beat until very stiff.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on greased sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Put cookies in oven; turn off heat and leave overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: turnip greens
directions: Clean turnip greens thoroughly to remove any sand.
Strip out heavy leaf vein.
Peel turnips; cut into small cubes.
Put greens, turnips and meat in saucepot (2 or 3-quart).
Add 3/4 cup water. Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Sift and mix well all the dry ingredients.
Mix all the liquid ingredients, then add to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: quick tomato-rice soup
directions: Combine soup, broth, rice, celery and pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 side-dish servings.

title: country-style skillet dinner
directions: About 40 minutes before serving in 10-inch skillet over high heat, in hot butter, cook meat until browned.
Stir in uncooked noodles, tomato sauce, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook, covered, over low heat 20 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese and heat, covered, until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings. 365 calories per serving.

title: party seafood casserole
directions: Parboil haddock and scallops until tender, about 10 minutes. Reserve liquid.
Remove any bones from haddock.
Melt margarine or butter.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper, then milk, fish, liquid and cream.
When smooth and thickened, add fish, scallops, shrimp (uncooked), crabmeat and sherry. Spoon mixture into buttered casserole and top with herb seasoning mix or buttered crumbs.

title: green beans
directions: Wash and trim ends off green beans; leave whole.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes.
Standing time 3 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: I
large
frypan,
cook
onion,
garlic,
eggplant
and mushrooms in
hot oil for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes,
tomato
sauce,
wine, carrot, parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and cook over high heat to reduce sauce to 5 cups.
Add Ricotta.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt; add.
Put soda in hot water and add last.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 8 minutes (or less).

title: award winning lemon sherbert("no birthday is complete without this one.")
directions: Combine cream cheese, half and half, and sugar until dissolved. Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, and lemon extract.
Whip cream slightly and add to mixture.
Add jello and milk.
Mix well. Freeze in 1 gallon freezer.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Add ingredients to the starter.
Add 1/2 cup of whatever
you like
(raisins,
dates
or nuts).
Pour into greased, floured and sugared pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: 1-2-3 relish
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Mash 1/2 banana.
Add the applesauce.
Stir in the plain yogurt.

title: x y z casserole
directions: Alternate layers of zucchini and yellow squash in microwave-safe dish.
Top with undrained pimiento; drizzle with margarine.
Microwave, covered with plastic wrap, on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Beat with wire whip until smooth.
Fry on hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: praline banana cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Add sugar, shortening, sour cream, bananas, eggs, and vanilla.
With mixer at low speed beat ingredients until mixed, constantly scrapping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes, occasionally scrapping bowl. Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool cake completely in pan on wire rack.

title: chicken, rice and spice dinner
directions: Shake flour in large cooking bag; add next 9 ingredients. Squeeze bag gently to mix.
Brush chicken with oil.
Arrange chicken and sausage on top of rice mixture.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 slots in bag and bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix with mixer the vanilla, butter flavoring, flour, cinnamon, sugar, soda, salt, eggs, butter and nutmeg until smooth.
Then add apples, nuts and raisins by hand.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine & milk in heavy big saucepan. Bring to a rapid boil. Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Take off heat. Mix in next 3 ingredients; then pour into greased 9 X 13 pan.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Pour apples and sugar in bowl.
Stir; let stand 1/2 hour.
Add oil and egg; blend.
Mix and add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 8 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: meat cheese roll
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into flat rectangle, about 10 x 14-inch on a piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over mixture; roll up like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal. Bake in a shallow pan 1 hour at 350°.
Drain excess fat; put remaining sauce over roll.
Add more shredded cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder and salt.
Add to batter with vanilla.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
In saucepan, heat milk and margarine just until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter, mixing well.
Batter is thin.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly. Add sugar and melted oleo.
Mix well. Add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: southwest salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine frozen corn, beans, pepper, onion and cilantro.
In a small jar make marinade; mix vinegar, oil, water and seasonings.
Pour over the bean/corn mixture, toss to blend and coat.
Refrigerate covered until the flavors blend, at least 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: drop biscuits
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk; stir until blended.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes 16 small or 8 large biscuits.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops on each side. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place rice in baking dish and pour the orange, apple and pineapple juice over.
Place chops on top (drippings too) and pour soup over all. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: honey garlic barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well; blend.
Place coals around edge of grill.
Place pieces of chicken on grill; skin side down, with larger pieces to the outside.
Baste bone side of chicken well and turn pieces over immediately.
Baste skin side of pieces well. Cover grill.
Turn and baste evenly 15 minutes until done.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in rolls. Cover with wax paper.
Refrigerate until cold.
Slice in thin slices.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown.
Do not overcook.

title: taco lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with taco seasoning.
In round 3-quart casserole dish, layer tortillas, meat and 1 cup cheese.
Make 2 layers, then top with chili beans, picante sauce and 1 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
(May mix or substitute Mozzarella cheese.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cut margarine into the flour and sugar.
Set 1 cup of the mixture aside.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Stir in milk lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (or until done). Top with Cool Whip.

title: unbelievable guacamole dip
directions: In mixing bowl add avocados.
Using a fork mash (slightly) the avocados.
Add lemon juice, garlic and red onion.
Season mixture with salt and pepper, hot sauce to spice it up.
I place Romas on grill and cook until blackened.
Rotate often.
Then peel skin.
I leave some on for that "smoked" flavor.
Chop and stir in avocado mixture.
I add jalapenos for a zing.
You can leave it out and add more hot sauce for spice.
Serve with cheese quesadillas, chips or with your favorite taco.

title: fudgy bittersweet brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat; remove from heat. Add chocolate. Stir occasionally until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture and nuts just until blended.
Spread evenly in prepared pan. Spread with remaining 1/4 cup nuts. Bake on center rack of oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until top is firm but not hard. Cool in pan.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cream and pineapple until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and pecans.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: russian angel wings
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add sugar and cream.
Beat until well blended.
Chill dough for easier handling.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch diamonds.
Make a slit in center of each diamond; slip one end through slit and pull gently to make a bow.
Fry in hot deep fat at 375°
until light brown. Drain.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add sugar, shortening, salt, beaten egg, extract and about 1/2 of flour, stirring slowly but continuously.
Let stand a short time or until it bubbles.
(This is important).

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Batter will be thick. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato-broccoli bake
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Stir in potatoes.
Turn 1/2 of mixture into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, top with broccoli.
Spoon remaining mixture over broccoli.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix bread crumbs and remaining butter.
Sprinkle around edges.
Bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut the bell peppers.
Mix hamburger, celery, rice, ketchup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder, pepper and egg. Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Place in square baking dish.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar and basil in 2 cup glass measure.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve sauce over peppers.

title: cream gravy
directions: *May use all milk.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler, add peanut butter and nuts; mix well.
Fold in marshmallows.
Spread in buttered 10 x 15-inch pan. Let cool to set up.
Cut into squares.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix eggs and water.
Add flour gradually; drop in boiling water for sauerkraut.
Cook for about 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Combine flour and spices in a plastic bag.
Shake chicken pieces in the bag to coat.
Melt butter; add pineapple juice, soy sauce and sugar.
Pour over chicken in a roaster.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Turn over and bake an additional 25 minutes. Ten minutes before serving, place a pineapple ring on each piece.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In mixing bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheets; chill for several days to let flavors blend.
These keep very well.
Makes about 40.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and egg; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool slightly for easier slicing.

title: krispy date balls
directions: Mix sugar, dates, margarine and vanilla flavoring in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and let cool slightly.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: nacho and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onion together.
Drain; cube cheese and mix cheese and mushroom soup together.
Cook in microwave until melted.
Stir in meat and onion.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix all other ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Slice cookies and layer (brown edge down lengthwise), on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook chocolate pudding according to directions.
Smooth hot pudding on top of cookie layer.
Layer with sliced cookies (not using brown edge slices). Cook vanilla pudding and smooth hot pudding on cookie layer. Layer with cookie slices.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkles.

title: apple streusel muffins
directions: In medium bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in apple; set aside.

title: chicken-chip bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Pile lightly in a 9-inch by 9-inch ovenware dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese, then the crushed potato chips.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
apples, sugar and pecans in a large bowl.	Let set for about 40 minutes.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, salt and soda together.
Add
slowly
to	apple mixture, stirring well.
Add cooking oil, eggs and vanilla; stir in using about 20 strokes. Pour
into tube pan which has only been greased on the bottom. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.	Cool and frost if desired.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Saute bacon until yellow, leave fat and add cabbage, onion and apple.
Cover and turn occasionally, until cabbage cooks down and moisture disappears.
Add sugar, salt, bay leaf and red wine. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with pork roast or pork chops.

title: moist butter cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and add eggs and pecans. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil sugar and water.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour sugar water over.
Cover with more pecans.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add tomatoes, green peppers, chili powder and garlic powder.
Let cool.
Add beans and heat again. It's real good and it's quick and easy.

title: granny pug's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Cook package of spaghetti in broth. May have to add can of chicken broth. Cook remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup water until sauce. Add 1 can mushroom soup.
Mix with other mixture and simmer.
Layer spaghetti, chicken mixture, cheese and repeat in that order, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seasoned chicken
directions: Wash chicken and skin it.
Mix bread crumbs and seasonings. Mix egg and water; cover cookie sheet with foil and cover with margarine.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg white and then bread crumbs.
Place on foil.
Dribble oil over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn over and bake another 30 minutes.

title: caramel cake and brown sugar frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 4 cake pans (9-inch round) or spray with vegetable oil and flour baking spray.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix all other ingredients together.
Put chicken in.
Cook 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tender at 350°.

title: sandy's taco dip
directions: Layer as listed in a glass pie plate.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: ring rice chantilly
directions: Stir together the sugar, salt and gelatin in a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Place over medium-low heat and stir constantly until mixture coats a metal spoon; set aside to completely cool.
Fold in rice and vanilla. Chill just until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in whipped cream. Coat a 1-quart ring mold lightly with cooking spray.
Gently spoon mixture into mold using spatula to smooth top.
Chill until firm. Carefully unmold onto serving plate.
Fill center with sliced and sweetened fruit, such as strawberries, raspberries or peaches.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel zucchini and slice thinly.
Put into frypan with oleo. Add garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Cook until transparent. Then place in a small casserole dish and add sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch; cook until thick. Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved and cool.
Add strawberries and place in baked pie shell.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter with mixer until creamy.
Add flour, sugar and vanilla, beating until blended.
Stir in pecans (dough will be stiff).
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool slightly.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, oil and both sugars together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in and blend.
Roll a teaspoon of soft dough into a ball, then roll in granulated sugar.
Press down
on a lightly greased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: margaritas
directions: Blend 1 1/2 minutes at low speed.
Serve in salt rimmed glasses.

title: strawberries
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, egg
and dates to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from heat.	Add Rice Krispies and nuts.	Shape
into
berries.
Roll
in
red sugar and put green sugar on	the end to form the stem.
Makes about 40.

title: cherie's famous chicken fricassee
directions: Brown chicken in oil in large pot.
Remove chicken.
Add mushrooms, garlic, and onions.
Saute until mushrooms are slightly brown and onions and garlic are golden.
Add vegetables, thyme, bay leaf, and bouillon cubes.
Add chicken back to pot.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender.
In a small bowl, stir flour and water until smooth.
Add to pot and stir until mixture thickens.

title: fruit torte
directions: Beat egg.
Add fruit cocktail with juice.
Sift together regular sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add to fruit and mix until blended.
Put in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cover with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (toothpick comes out clean).
Serve at room temperature.
Best if prepared day before.

title: chicken-chip bake
directions: First, preheat oven to 425°.
Second, combine first 8 ingredients, then pile lightly in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese, then sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes.
It serves 5 to 6.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and mash.
Combine potatoes and next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: pork hash
directions: Boil roast until completely cooked and tender.
Remove roast from broth; cool and cut in small pieces.
Strain broth and chill; remove excess fat.
Place roast back into strained broth and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 3 or 4 hours.
Stir frequently.
Delicious over rice.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: rocky road chocolate pie
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding and 3 cups of milk as directed on package.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Add most of the chocolate chips, nuts and marshmallows and swirl caramel sauce into pudding.
Pour into pie shell and top with remaining nuts, marshmallows and chips.
Chill at least 3 hours and serve with Cool Whip.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: blender ketchup
directions: Quarter tomatoes; remove stem ends.
Add peppers, seeded, and cut into strips.
Add onions, peeled and quartered.
Mix.
Put vegetables in blender, filling jar 3/4 full.
Blend on high 4 seconds.
Pour into large kettle or roasting pan.
Repeat until all vegetables are blended.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices tied loosely in bag.
Simmer, uncovered, in a 325° oven until reduced half.
Remove spices.
Seal immediately in hot sterilized jars.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chocolate caramel oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in processor.
Add butter and cut in using on/off turns until crumbs begin to stick together.
Press all but 2 cups crumb mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over. Set crust aside.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes but do not mash them. Combine all ingredients and serve cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line oven dish or pan with foil.
Place pork chops along edge. Slice potatoes in center.
Slice onions over potatoes.
Slice margarine over onions; salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and seal. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal. Store in covered container at room temperature.
Makes 29 cups.

title: quick hobo dinners
directions: Instead of individually wrapping each dinner in aluminum foil, just lay the patties in the bottom of an oven cooking dish.
Salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Place an onion slice on top of each patty.
Top and surround with potatoes, carrots and margarine. Salt and pepper to please.
Cook for 1 hour at 400°.
Serve with ketchup or A.1. steak sauce.

title: hot chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in frypan and stir-fry.
